2277/// ParseIndexList - This parses the index list for an insert/extractvalue
2278/// instruction. This sets AteExtraComma in the case where we eat an extra
2279/// comma at the end of the line and find that it is followed by metadata.
2280/// Clients that don't allow metadata can call the version of this function that
2281/// only takes one argument.
2282///
2283/// ParseIndexList
2284/// ::= (',' uint32)+
2285///
2286bool LLParser::ParseIndexList(SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &Indices,
2287 bool &AteExtraComma) {
2288 AteExtraComma = false;
2289
2290 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::comma)
2291 return TokError("expected ',' as start of index list");
2292
2293 while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
2294 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar) {
2295 if (Indices.empty()) return TokError("expected index");
2296 AteExtraComma = true;
2297 return false;
2298 }
2299 unsigned Idx = 0;
2300 if (ParseUInt32(Idx)) return true;
2301 Indices.push_back(Idx);
2302 }
2303
2304 return false;
2305}
2306
2307//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2308// Type Parsing.
2309//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2310
2311/// ParseType - Parse a type.
2312bool LLParser::ParseType(Type *&Result, const Twine &Msg, bool AllowVoid) {
2313 SMLoc TypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2314 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
2315 default:
2316 return TokError(Msg);
2317 case lltok::Type:
2318 // Type ::= 'float' | 'void' (etc)
2319 Result = Lex.getTyVal();
2320 Lex.Lex();
2321 break;
2322 case lltok::lbrace:
2323 // Type ::= StructType
2324 if (ParseAnonStructType(Result, false))
2325 return true;
2326 break;
2327 case lltok::lsquare:
2328 // Type ::= '[' ... ']'
2329 Lex.Lex(); // eat the lsquare.
2330 if (ParseArrayVectorType(Result, false))
2331 return true;
2332 break;
2333 case lltok::less: // Either vector or packed struct.
2334 // Type ::= '<' ... '>'
2335 Lex.Lex();
2336 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::lbrace) {
2337 if (ParseAnonStructType(Result, true) ||
2338 ParseToken(lltok::greater, "expected '>' at end of packed struct"))
2339 return true;
2340 } else if (ParseArrayVectorType(Result, true))
2341 return true;
2342 break;
2343 case lltok::LocalVar: {
2344 // Type ::= %foo
2345 std::pair<Type*, LocTy> &Entry = NamedTypes[Lex.getStrVal()];
2346
2347 // If the type hasn't been defined yet, create a forward definition and
2348 // remember where that forward def'n was seen (in case it never is defined).
2349 if (!Entry.first) {
2350 Entry.first = StructType::create(Context, Lex.getStrVal());
2351 Entry.second = Lex.getLoc();
2352 }
2353 Result = Entry.first;
2354 Lex.Lex();
2355 break;
2356 }
2357
2358 case lltok::LocalVarID: {
2359 // Type ::= %4
2360 std::pair<Type*, LocTy> &Entry = NumberedTypes[Lex.getUIntVal()];
2361
2362 // If the type hasn't been defined yet, create a forward definition and
2363 // remember where that forward def'n was seen (in case it never is defined).
2364 if (!Entry.first) {
2365 Entry.first = StructType::create(Context);
2366 Entry.second = Lex.getLoc();
2367 }
2368 Result = Entry.first;
2369 Lex.Lex();
2370 break;
2371 }
2372 }
2373
2374 // Parse the type suffixes.
2375 while (true) {
2376 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
2377 // End of type.
2378 default:
2379 if (!AllowVoid && Result->isVoidTy())
2380 return Error(TypeLoc, "void type only allowed for function results");
2381 return false;
2382
2383 // Type ::= Type '*'
2384 case lltok::star:
2385 if (Result->isLabelTy())
2386 return TokError("basic block pointers are invalid");
2387 if (Result->isVoidTy())
2388 return TokError("pointers to void are invalid - use i8* instead");
2389 if (!PointerType::isValidElementType(Result))
2390 return TokError("pointer to this type is invalid");
2391 Result = PointerType::getUnqual(Result);
2392 Lex.Lex();
2393 break;
2394
2395 // Type ::= Type 'addrspace' '(' uint32 ')' '*'
2396 case lltok::kw_addrspace: {
2397 if (Result->isLabelTy())
2398 return TokError("basic block pointers are invalid");
2399 if (Result->isVoidTy())
2400 return TokError("pointers to void are invalid; use i8* instead");
2401 if (!PointerType::isValidElementType(Result))
2402 return TokError("pointer to this type is invalid");
2403 unsigned AddrSpace;
2404 if (ParseOptionalAddrSpace(AddrSpace) ||
2405 ParseToken(lltok::star, "expected '*' in address space"))
2406 return true;
2407
2408 Result = PointerType::get(Result, AddrSpace);
2409 break;
2410 }
2411
2412 /// Types '(' ArgTypeListI ')' OptFuncAttrs
2413 case lltok::lparen:
2414 if (ParseFunctionType(Result))
2415 return true;
2416 break;
2417 }
2418 }
2419}
2420
2421/// ParseParameterList
2422/// ::= '(' ')'
2423/// ::= '(' Arg (',' Arg)* ')'
2424/// Arg
2425/// ::= Type OptionalAttributes Value OptionalAttributes
2426bool LLParser::ParseParameterList(SmallVectorImpl<ParamInfo> &ArgList,
2427 PerFunctionState &PFS, bool IsMustTailCall,
2428 bool InVarArgsFunc) {
2429 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in call"))
2430 return true;
2431
2432 while (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rparen) {
2433 // If this isn't the first argument, we need a comma.
2434 if (!ArgList.empty() &&
2435 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' in argument list"))
2436 return true;
2437
2438 // Parse an ellipsis if this is a musttail call in a variadic function.
2439 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::dotdotdot) {
2440 const char *Msg = "unexpected ellipsis in argument list for ";
2441 if (!IsMustTailCall)
2442 return TokError(Twine(Msg) + "non-musttail call");
2443 if (!InVarArgsFunc)
2444 return TokError(Twine(Msg) + "musttail call in non-varargs function");
2445 Lex.Lex(); // Lex the '...', it is purely for readability.
2446 return ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' at end of argument list");
2447 }
2448
2449 // Parse the argument.
2450 LocTy ArgLoc;
2451 Type *ArgTy = nullptr;
2452 AttrBuilder ArgAttrs;
2453 Value *V;
2454 if (ParseType(ArgTy, ArgLoc))
2455 return true;
2456
2457 if (ArgTy->isMetadataTy()) {
2458 if (ParseMetadataAsValue(V, PFS))
2459 return true;
2460 } else {
2461 // Otherwise, handle normal operands.
2462 if (ParseOptionalParamAttrs(ArgAttrs) || ParseValue(ArgTy, V, PFS))
2463 return true;
2464 }
2465 ArgList.push_back(ParamInfo(
2466 ArgLoc, V, AttributeSet::get(V->getContext(), ArgAttrs)));
2467 }
2468
2469 if (IsMustTailCall && InVarArgsFunc)
2470 return TokError("expected '...' at end of argument list for musttail call "
2471 "in varargs function");
2472
2473 Lex.Lex(); // Lex the ')'.
2474 return false;
2475}
2476
2477/// ParseByValWithOptionalType
2478/// ::= byval
2479/// ::= byval(<ty>)
2480bool LLParser::ParseByValWithOptionalType(Type *&Result) {
2481 Result = nullptr;
2482 if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_byval))
2483 return true;
2484 if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::lparen))
2485 return false;
2486 if (ParseType(Result))
2487 return true;
2488 if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::rparen))
2489 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected ')'");
2490 return false;
2491}
2492
2493/// ParseOptionalOperandBundles
2494/// ::= /*empty*/
2495/// ::= '[' OperandBundle [, OperandBundle ]* ']'
2496///
2497/// OperandBundle
2498/// ::= bundle-tag '(' ')'
2499/// ::= bundle-tag '(' Type Value [, Type Value ]* ')'
2500///
2501/// bundle-tag ::= String Constant
2502bool LLParser::ParseOptionalOperandBundles(
2503 SmallVectorImpl<OperandBundleDef> &BundleList, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
2504 LocTy BeginLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2505 if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::lsquare))
2506 return false;
2507
2508 while (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rsquare) {
2509 // If this isn't the first operand bundle, we need a comma.
2510 if (!BundleList.empty() &&
2511 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' in input list"))
2512 return true;
2513
2514 std::string Tag;
2515 if (ParseStringConstant(Tag))
2516 return true;
2517
2518 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in operand bundle"))
2519 return true;
2520
2521 std::vector<Value *> Inputs;
2522 while (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rparen) {
2523 // If this isn't the first input, we need a comma.
2524 if (!Inputs.empty() &&
2525 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' in input list"))
2526 return true;
2527
2528 Type *Ty = nullptr;
2529 Value *Input = nullptr;
2530 if (ParseType(Ty) || ParseValue(Ty, Input, PFS))
2531 return true;
2532 Inputs.push_back(Input);
2533 }
2534
2535 BundleList.emplace_back(std::move(Tag), std::move(Inputs));
2536
2537 Lex.Lex(); // Lex the ')'.
2538 }
2539
2540 if (BundleList.empty())
2541 return Error(BeginLoc, "operand bundle set must not be empty");
2542
2543 Lex.Lex(); // Lex the ']'.
2544 return false;
2545}
2546
2547/// ParseArgumentList - Parse the argument list for a function type or function
2548/// prototype.
2549/// ::= '(' ArgTypeListI ')'
2550/// ArgTypeListI
2551/// ::= /*empty*/
2552/// ::= '...'
2553/// ::= ArgTypeList ',' '...'
2554/// ::= ArgType (',' ArgType)*
2555///
2556bool LLParser::ParseArgumentList(SmallVectorImpl<ArgInfo> &ArgList,
2557 bool &isVarArg){
2558 isVarArg = false;
2559 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::lparen);
2560 Lex.Lex(); // eat the (.
2561
2562 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::rparen) {
2563 // empty
2564 } else if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::dotdotdot) {
2565 isVarArg = true;
2566 Lex.Lex();
2567 } else {
2568 LocTy TypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2569 Type *ArgTy = nullptr;
2570 AttrBuilder Attrs;
2571 std::string Name;
2572
2573 if (ParseType(ArgTy) ||
2574 ParseOptionalParamAttrs(Attrs)) return true;
2575
2576 if (ArgTy->isVoidTy())
2577 return Error(TypeLoc, "argument can not have void type");
2578
2579 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LocalVar) {
2580 Name = Lex.getStrVal();
2581 Lex.Lex();
2582 }
2583
2584 if (!FunctionType::isValidArgumentType(ArgTy))
2585 return Error(TypeLoc, "invalid type for function argument");
2586
2587 ArgList.emplace_back(TypeLoc, ArgTy,
2588 AttributeSet::get(ArgTy->getContext(), Attrs),
2589 std::move(Name));
2590
2591 while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
2592 // Handle ... at end of arg list.
2593 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::dotdotdot)) {
2594 isVarArg = true;
2595 break;
2596 }
2597
2598 // Otherwise must be an argument type.
2599 TypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2600 if (ParseType(ArgTy) || ParseOptionalParamAttrs(Attrs)) return true;
2601
2602 if (ArgTy->isVoidTy())
2603 return Error(TypeLoc, "argument can not have void type");
2604
2605 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::LocalVar) {
2606 Name = Lex.getStrVal();
2607 Lex.Lex();
2608 } else {
2609 Name = "";
2610 }
2611
2612 if (!ArgTy->isFirstClassType())
2613 return Error(TypeLoc, "invalid type for function argument");
2614
2615 ArgList.emplace_back(TypeLoc, ArgTy,
2616 AttributeSet::get(ArgTy->getContext(), Attrs),
2617 std::move(Name));
2618 }
2619 }
2620
2621 return ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' at end of argument list");
2622}
2623
2624/// ParseFunctionType
2625/// ::= Type ArgumentList OptionalAttrs
2626bool LLParser::ParseFunctionType(Type *&Result) {
2627 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::lparen);
2628
2629 if (!FunctionType::isValidReturnType(Result))
2630 return TokError("invalid function return type");
2631
2632 SmallVector<ArgInfo, 8> ArgList;
2633 bool isVarArg;
2634 if (ParseArgumentList(ArgList, isVarArg))
2635 return true;
2636
2637 // Reject names on the arguments lists.
2638 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2639 if (!ArgList[i].Name.empty())
2640 return Error(ArgList[i].Loc, "argument name invalid in function type");
2641 if (ArgList[i].Attrs.hasAttributes())
2642 return Error(ArgList[i].Loc,
2643 "argument attributes invalid in function type");
2644 }
2645
2646 SmallVector<Type*, 16> ArgListTy;
2647 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgList.size(); i != e; ++i)
2648 ArgListTy.push_back(ArgList[i].Ty);
2649
2650 Result = FunctionType::get(Result, ArgListTy, isVarArg);
2651 return false;
2652}
2653
2654/// ParseAnonStructType - Parse an anonymous struct type, which is inlined into
2655/// other structs.
2656bool LLParser::ParseAnonStructType(Type *&Result, bool Packed) {
2657 SmallVector<Type*, 8> Elts;
2658 if (ParseStructBody(Elts)) return true;
2659
2660 Result = StructType::get(Context, Elts, Packed);
2661 return false;
2662}
2663
2664/// ParseStructDefinition - Parse a struct in a 'type' definition.
2665bool LLParser::ParseStructDefinition(SMLoc TypeLoc, StringRef Name,
2666 std::pair<Type*, LocTy> &Entry,
2667 Type *&ResultTy) {
2668 // If the type was already defined, diagnose the redefinition.
2669 if (Entry.first && !Entry.second.isValid())
2670 return Error(TypeLoc, "redefinition of type");
2671
2672 // If we have opaque, just return without filling in the definition for the
2673 // struct. This counts as a definition as far as the .ll file goes.
2674 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_opaque)) {
2675 // This type is being defined, so clear the location to indicate this.
2676 Entry.second = SMLoc();
2677
2678 // If this type number has never been uttered, create it.
2679 if (!Entry.first)
2680 Entry.first = StructType::create(Context, Name);
2681 ResultTy = Entry.first;
2682 return false;
2683 }
2684
2685 // If the type starts with '<', then it is either a packed struct or a vector.
2686 bool isPacked = EatIfPresent(lltok::less);
2687
2688 // If we don't have a struct, then we have a random type alias, which we
2689 // accept for compatibility with old files. These types are not allowed to be
2690 // forward referenced and not allowed to be recursive.
2691 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::lbrace) {
2692 if (Entry.first)
2693 return Error(TypeLoc, "forward references to non-struct type");
2694
2695 ResultTy = nullptr;
2696 if (isPacked)
2697 return ParseArrayVectorType(ResultTy, true);
2698 return ParseType(ResultTy);
2699 }
2700
2701 // This type is being defined, so clear the location to indicate this.
2702 Entry.second = SMLoc();
2703
2704 // If this type number has never been uttered, create it.
2705 if (!Entry.first)
2706 Entry.first = StructType::create(Context, Name);
2707
2708 StructType *STy = cast<StructType>(Entry.first);
2709
2710 SmallVector<Type*, 8> Body;
2711 if (ParseStructBody(Body) ||
2712 (isPacked && ParseToken(lltok::greater, "expected '>' in packed struct")))
2713 return true;
2714
2715 STy->setBody(Body, isPacked);
2716 ResultTy = STy;
2717 return false;
2718}
2719
2720/// ParseStructType: Handles packed and unpacked types. </> parsed elsewhere.
2721/// StructType
2722/// ::= '{' '}'
2723/// ::= '{' Type (',' Type)* '}'
2724/// ::= '<' '{' '}' '>'
2725/// ::= '<' '{' Type (',' Type)* '}' '>'
2726bool LLParser::ParseStructBody(SmallVectorImpl<Type*> &Body) {
2727 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::lbrace);
2728 Lex.Lex(); // Consume the '{'
2729
2730 // Handle the empty struct.
2731 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::rbrace))
2732 return false;
2733
2734 LocTy EltTyLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2735 Type *Ty = nullptr;
2736 if (ParseType(Ty)) return true;
2737 Body.push_back(Ty);
2738
2739 if (!StructType::isValidElementType(Ty))
2740 return Error(EltTyLoc, "invalid element type for struct");
2741
2742 while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
2743 EltTyLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2744 if (ParseType(Ty)) return true;
2745
2746 if (!StructType::isValidElementType(Ty))
2747 return Error(EltTyLoc, "invalid element type for struct");
2748
2749 Body.push_back(Ty);
2750 }
2751
2752 return ParseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected '}' at end of struct");
2753}
2754
2755/// ParseArrayVectorType - Parse an array or vector type, assuming the first
2756/// token has already been consumed.
2757/// Type
2758/// ::= '[' APSINTVAL 'x' Types ']'
2759/// ::= '<' APSINTVAL 'x' Types '>'
2760bool LLParser::ParseArrayVectorType(Type *&Result, bool isVector) {
2761 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt || Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned() ||
2762 Lex.getAPSIntVal().getBitWidth() > 64)
2763 return TokError("expected number in address space");
2764
2765 LocTy SizeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2766 uint64_t Size = Lex.getAPSIntVal().getZExtValue();
2767 Lex.Lex();
2768
2769 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_x, "expected 'x' after element count"))
2770 return true;
2771
2772 LocTy TypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
2773 Type *EltTy = nullptr;
2774 if (ParseType(EltTy)) return true;
2775
2776 if (ParseToken(isVector ? lltok::greater : lltok::rsquare,
2777 "expected end of sequential type"))
2778 return true;
2779
2780 if (isVector) {
2781 if (Size == 0)
2782 return Error(SizeLoc, "zero element vector is illegal");
2783 if ((unsigned)Size != Size)
2784 return Error(SizeLoc, "size too large for vector");
2785 if (!VectorType::isValidElementType(EltTy))
2786 return Error(TypeLoc, "invalid vector element type");
2787 Result = VectorType::get(EltTy, unsigned(Size));
2788 } else {
2789 if (!ArrayType::isValidElementType(EltTy))
2790 return Error(TypeLoc, "invalid array element type");
2791 Result = ArrayType::get(EltTy, Size);
2792 }
2793 return false;
2794}

2796//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2797// Function Semantic Analysis.
2798//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2799
2800LLParser::PerFunctionState::PerFunctionState(LLParser &p, Function &f,
2801 int functionNumber)
2802 : P(p), F(f), FunctionNumber(functionNumber) {
2803
2804 // Insert unnamed arguments into the NumberedVals list.
2805 for (Argument &A : F.args())
2806 if (!A.hasName())
2807 NumberedVals.push_back(&A);
2808}
2809
2810LLParser::PerFunctionState::~PerFunctionState() {
2811 // If there were any forward referenced non-basicblock values, delete them.
2812
2813 for (const auto &P : ForwardRefVals) {
2814 if (isa<BasicBlock>(P.second.first))
2815 continue;
2816 P.second.first->replaceAllUsesWith(
2817 UndefValue::get(P.second.first->getType()));
2818 P.second.first->deleteValue();
2819 }
2820
2821 for (const auto &P : ForwardRefValIDs) {
2822 if (isa<BasicBlock>(P.second.first))
2823 continue;
2824 P.second.first->replaceAllUsesWith(
2825 UndefValue::get(P.second.first->getType()));
2826 P.second.first->deleteValue();
2827 }
2828}
2829
2830bool LLParser::PerFunctionState::FinishFunction() {
2831 if (!ForwardRefVals.empty())
2832 return P.Error(ForwardRefVals.begin()->second.second,
2833 "use of undefined value '%" + ForwardRefVals.begin()->first +
2834 "'");
2835 if (!ForwardRefValIDs.empty())
2836 return P.Error(ForwardRefValIDs.begin()->second.second,
2837 "use of undefined value '%" +
2838 Twine(ForwardRefValIDs.begin()->first) + "'");
2839 return false;
2840}
2841
2842/// GetVal - Get a value with the specified name or ID, creating a
2843/// forward reference record if needed. This can return null if the value
2844/// exists but does not have the right type.
2845Value *LLParser::PerFunctionState::GetVal(const std::string &Name, Type *Ty,
2846 LocTy Loc, bool IsCall) {
2847 // Look this name up in the normal function symbol table.
2848 Value *Val = F.getValueSymbolTable()->lookup(Name);
2849
2850 // If this is a forward reference for the value, see if we already created a
2851 // forward ref record.
2852 if (!Val) {
2853 auto I = ForwardRefVals.find(Name);
2854 if (I != ForwardRefVals.end())
2855 Val = I->second.first;
2856 }
2857
2858 // If we have the value in the symbol table or fwd-ref table, return it.
2859 if (Val)
2860 return P.checkValidVariableType(Loc, "%" + Name, Ty, Val, IsCall);
2861
2862 // Don't make placeholders with invalid type.
2863 if (!Ty->isFirstClassType()) {
2864 P.Error(Loc, "invalid use of a non-first-class type");
2865 return nullptr;
2866 }
2867
2868 // Otherwise, create a new forward reference for this value and remember it.
2869 Value *FwdVal;
2870 if (Ty->isLabelTy()) {
2871 FwdVal = BasicBlock::Create(F.getContext(), Name, &F);
2872 } else {
2873 FwdVal = new Argument(Ty, Name);
2874 }
2875
2876 ForwardRefVals[Name] = std::make_pair(FwdVal, Loc);
2877 return FwdVal;
2878}
2879
2880Value *LLParser::PerFunctionState::GetVal(unsigned ID, Type *Ty, LocTy Loc,
2881 bool IsCall) {
2882 // Look this name up in the normal function symbol table.
2883 Value *Val = ID < NumberedVals.size() ? NumberedVals[ID] : nullptr;
2884
2885 // If this is a forward reference for the value, see if we already created a
2886 // forward ref record.
2887 if (!Val) {
2888 auto I = ForwardRefValIDs.find(ID);
2889 if (I != ForwardRefValIDs.end())
2890 Val = I->second.first;
2891 }
2892
2893 // If we have the value in the symbol table or fwd-ref table, return it.
2894 if (Val)
2895 return P.checkValidVariableType(Loc, "%" + Twine(ID), Ty, Val, IsCall);
2896
2897 if (!Ty->isFirstClassType()) {
2898 P.Error(Loc, "invalid use of a non-first-class type");
2899 return nullptr;
2900 }
2901
2902 // Otherwise, create a new forward reference for this value and remember it.
2903 Value *FwdVal;
2904 if (Ty->isLabelTy()) {
2905 FwdVal = BasicBlock::Create(F.getContext(), "", &F);
2906 } else {
2907 FwdVal = new Argument(Ty);
2908 }
2909
2910 ForwardRefValIDs[ID] = std::make_pair(FwdVal, Loc);
2911 return FwdVal;
2912}
2913
2914/// SetInstName - After an instruction is parsed and inserted into its
2915/// basic block, this installs its name.
2916bool LLParser::PerFunctionState::SetInstName(int NameID,
2917 const std::string &NameStr,
2918 LocTy NameLoc, Instruction *Inst) {
2919 // If this instruction has void type, it cannot have a name or ID specified.
2920 if (Inst->getType()->isVoidTy()) {
2921 if (NameID != -1 || !NameStr.empty())
2922 return P.Error(NameLoc, "instructions returning void cannot have a name");
2923 return false;
2924 }
2925
2926 // If this was a numbered instruction, verify that the instruction is the
2927 // expected value and resolve any forward references.
2928 if (NameStr.empty()) {
2929 // If neither a name nor an ID was specified, just use the next ID.
2930 if (NameID == -1)
2931 NameID = NumberedVals.size();
2932
2933 if (unsigned(NameID) != NumberedVals.size())
2934 return P.Error(NameLoc, "instruction expected to be numbered '%" +
2935 Twine(NumberedVals.size()) + "'");
2936
2937 auto FI = ForwardRefValIDs.find(NameID);
2938 if (FI != ForwardRefValIDs.end()) {
2939 Value *Sentinel = FI->second.first;
2940 if (Sentinel->getType() != Inst->getType())
2941 return P.Error(NameLoc, "instruction forward referenced with type '" +
2942 getTypeString(FI->second.first->getType()) + "'");
2943
2944 Sentinel->replaceAllUsesWith(Inst);
2945 Sentinel->deleteValue();
2946 ForwardRefValIDs.erase(FI);
2947 }
2948
2949 NumberedVals.push_back(Inst);
2950 return false;
2951 }
2952
2953 // Otherwise, the instruction had a name. Resolve forward refs and set it.
2954 auto FI = ForwardRefVals.find(NameStr);
2955 if (FI != ForwardRefVals.end()) {
2956 Value *Sentinel = FI->second.first;
2957 if (Sentinel->getType() != Inst->getType())
2958 return P.Error(NameLoc, "instruction forward referenced with type '" +
2959 getTypeString(FI->second.first->getType()) + "'");
2960
2961 Sentinel->replaceAllUsesWith(Inst);
2962 Sentinel->deleteValue();
2963 ForwardRefVals.erase(FI);
2964 }
2965
2966 // Set the name on the instruction.
2967 Inst->setName(NameStr);
2968
2969 if (Inst->getName() != NameStr)
2970 return P.Error(NameLoc, "multiple definition of local value named '" +
2971 NameStr + "'");
2972 return false;
2973}
2974
2975/// GetBB - Get a basic block with the specified name or ID, creating a
2976/// forward reference record if needed.
2977BasicBlock *LLParser::PerFunctionState::GetBB(const std::string &Name,
2978 LocTy Loc) {
2979 return dyn_cast_or_null<BasicBlock>(
2980 GetVal(Name, Type::getLabelTy(F.getContext()), Loc, /*IsCall=*/false));
2981}
2982
2983BasicBlock *LLParser::PerFunctionState::GetBB(unsigned ID, LocTy Loc) {
2984 return dyn_cast_or_null<BasicBlock>(
2985 GetVal(ID, Type::getLabelTy(F.getContext()), Loc, /*IsCall=*/false));
2986}
2987
2988/// DefineBB - Define the specified basic block, which is either named or
2989/// unnamed. If there is an error, this returns null otherwise it returns
2990/// the block being defined.
2991BasicBlock *LLParser::PerFunctionState::DefineBB(const std::string &Name,
2992 int NameID, LocTy Loc) {
2993 BasicBlock *BB;
2994 if (Name.empty()) {
2995 if (NameID != -1 && unsigned(NameID) != NumberedVals.size()) {
2996 P.Error(Loc, "label expected to be numbered '" +
2997 Twine(NumberedVals.size()) + "'");
2998 return nullptr;
2999 }
3000 BB = GetBB(NumberedVals.size(), Loc);
3001 if (!BB) {
3002 P.Error(Loc, "unable to create block numbered '" +
3003 Twine(NumberedVals.size()) + "'");
3004 return nullptr;
3005 }
3006 } else {
3007 BB = GetBB(Name, Loc);
3008 if (!BB) {
3009 P.Error(Loc, "unable to create block named '" + Name + "'");
3010 return nullptr;
3011 }
3012 }
3013
3014 // Move the block to the end of the function. Forward ref'd blocks are
3015 // inserted wherever they happen to be referenced.
3016 F.getBasicBlockList().splice(F.end(), F.getBasicBlockList(), BB);
3017
3018 // Remove the block from forward ref sets.
3019 if (Name.empty()) {
3020 ForwardRefValIDs.erase(NumberedVals.size());
3021 NumberedVals.push_back(BB);
3022 } else {
3023 // BB forward references are already in the function symbol table.
3024 ForwardRefVals.erase(Name);
3025 }
3026
3027 return BB;
3028}
3029
3030//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3031// Constants.
3032//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3033
3034/// ParseValID - Parse an abstract value that doesn't necessarily have a
3035/// type implied. For example, if we parse "4" we don't know what integer type
3036/// it has. The value will later be combined with its type and checked for
3037/// sanity. PFS is used to convert function-local operands of metadata (since
3038/// metadata operands are not just parsed here but also converted to values).
3039/// PFS can be null when we are not parsing metadata values inside a function.
3040bool LLParser::ParseValID(ValID &ID, PerFunctionState *PFS) {
3041 ID.Loc = Lex.getLoc();
3042 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
3043 default: return TokError("expected value token");
3044 case lltok::GlobalID: // @42
3045 ID.UIntVal = Lex.getUIntVal();
3046 ID.Kind = ValID::t_GlobalID;
3047 break;
3048 case lltok::GlobalVar: // @foo
3049 ID.StrVal = Lex.getStrVal();
3050 ID.Kind = ValID::t_GlobalName;
3051 break;
3052 case lltok::LocalVarID: // %42
3053 ID.UIntVal = Lex.getUIntVal();
3054 ID.Kind = ValID::t_LocalID;
3055 break;
3056 case lltok::LocalVar: // %foo
3057 ID.StrVal = Lex.getStrVal();
3058 ID.Kind = ValID::t_LocalName;
3059 break;
3060 case lltok::APSInt:
3061 ID.APSIntVal = Lex.getAPSIntVal();
3062 ID.Kind = ValID::t_APSInt;
3063 break;
3064 case lltok::APFloat:
3065 ID.APFloatVal = Lex.getAPFloatVal();
3066 ID.Kind = ValID::t_APFloat;
3067 break;
3068 case lltok::kw_true:
3069 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantInt::getTrue(Context);
3070 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3071 break;
3072 case lltok::kw_false:
3073 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantInt::getFalse(Context);
3074 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3075 break;
3076 case lltok::kw_null: ID.Kind = ValID::t_Null; break;
3077 case lltok::kw_undef: ID.Kind = ValID::t_Undef; break;
3078 case lltok::kw_zeroinitializer: ID.Kind = ValID::t_Zero; break;
3079 case lltok::kw_none: ID.Kind = ValID::t_None; break;
3080
3081 case lltok::lbrace: {
3082 // ValID ::= '{' ConstVector '}'
3083 Lex.Lex();
3084 SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
3085 if (ParseGlobalValueVector(Elts) ||
3086 ParseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected end of struct constant"))
3087 return true;
3088
3089 ID.ConstantStructElts = make_unique<Constant *[]>(Elts.size());
3090 ID.UIntVal = Elts.size();
3091 memcpy(ID.ConstantStructElts.get(), Elts.data(),
3092 Elts.size() * sizeof(Elts[0]));
3093 ID.Kind = ValID::t_ConstantStruct;
3094 return false;
3095 }
3096 case lltok::less: {
3097 // ValID ::= '<' ConstVector '>' --> Vector.
3098 // ValID ::= '<' '{' ConstVector '}' '>' --> Packed Struct.
3099 Lex.Lex();
3100 bool isPackedStruct = EatIfPresent(lltok::lbrace);
3101
3102 SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
3103 LocTy FirstEltLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3104 if (ParseGlobalValueVector(Elts) ||
3105 (isPackedStruct &&
3106 ParseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected end of packed struct")) ||
3107 ParseToken(lltok::greater, "expected end of constant"))
3108 return true;
3109
3110 if (isPackedStruct) {
3111 ID.ConstantStructElts = make_unique<Constant *[]>(Elts.size());
3112 memcpy(ID.ConstantStructElts.get(), Elts.data(),
3113 Elts.size() * sizeof(Elts[0]));
3114 ID.UIntVal = Elts.size();
3115 ID.Kind = ValID::t_PackedConstantStruct;
3116 return false;
3117 }
3118
3119 if (Elts.empty())
3120 return Error(ID.Loc, "constant vector must not be empty");
3121
3122 if (!Elts[0]->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
3123 !Elts[0]->getType()->isFloatingPointTy() &&
3124 !Elts[0]->getType()->isPointerTy())
3125 return Error(FirstEltLoc,
3126 "vector elements must have integer, pointer or floating point type");
3127
3128 // Verify that all the vector elements have the same type.
3129 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Elts.size(); i != e; ++i)
3130 if (Elts[i]->getType() != Elts[0]->getType())
3131 return Error(FirstEltLoc,
3132 "vector element #" + Twine(i) +
3133 " is not of type '" + getTypeString(Elts[0]->getType()));
3134
3135 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantVector::get(Elts);
3136 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3137 return false;
3138 }
3139 case lltok::lsquare: { // Array Constant
3140 Lex.Lex();
3141 SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
3142 LocTy FirstEltLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3143 if (ParseGlobalValueVector(Elts) ||
3144 ParseToken(lltok::rsquare, "expected end of array constant"))
3145 return true;
3146
3147 // Handle empty element.
3148 if (Elts.empty()) {
3149 // Use undef instead of an array because it's inconvenient to determine
3150 // the element type at this point, there being no elements to examine.
3151 ID.Kind = ValID::t_EmptyArray;
3152 return false;
3153 }
3154
3155 if (!Elts[0]->getType()->isFirstClassType())
3156 return Error(FirstEltLoc, "invalid array element type: " +
3157 getTypeString(Elts[0]->getType()));
3158
3159 ArrayType *ATy = ArrayType::get(Elts[0]->getType(), Elts.size());
3160
3161 // Verify all elements are correct type!
3162 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Elts.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3163 if (Elts[i]->getType() != Elts[0]->getType())
3164 return Error(FirstEltLoc,
3165 "array element #" + Twine(i) +
3166 " is not of type '" + getTypeString(Elts[0]->getType()));
3167 }
3168
3169 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantArray::get(ATy, Elts);
3170 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3171 return false;
3172 }
3173 case lltok::kw_c: // c "foo"
3174 Lex.Lex();
3175 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantDataArray::getString(Context, Lex.getStrVal(),
3176 false);
3177 if (ParseToken(lltok::StringConstant, "expected string")) return true;
3178 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3179 return false;
3180
3181 case lltok::kw_asm: {
3182 // ValID ::= 'asm' SideEffect? AlignStack? IntelDialect? STRINGCONSTANT ','
3183 // STRINGCONSTANT
3184 bool HasSideEffect, AlignStack, AsmDialect;
3185 Lex.Lex();
3186 if (ParseOptionalToken(lltok::kw_sideeffect, HasSideEffect) ||
3187 ParseOptionalToken(lltok::kw_alignstack, AlignStack) ||
3188 ParseOptionalToken(lltok::kw_inteldialect, AsmDialect) ||
3189 ParseStringConstant(ID.StrVal) ||
3190 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in inline asm expression") ||
3191 ParseToken(lltok::StringConstant, "expected constraint string"))
3192 return true;
3193 ID.StrVal2 = Lex.getStrVal();
3194 ID.UIntVal = unsigned(HasSideEffect) | (unsigned(AlignStack)<<1) |
3195 (unsigned(AsmDialect)<<2);
3196 ID.Kind = ValID::t_InlineAsm;
3197 return false;
3198 }
3199
3200 case lltok::kw_blockaddress: {
3201 // ValID ::= 'blockaddress' '(' @foo ',' %bar ')'
3202 Lex.Lex();
3203
3204 ValID Fn, Label;
3205
3206 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in block address expression") ||
3207 ParseValID(Fn) ||
3208 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in block address expression")||
3209 ParseValID(Label) ||
3210 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in block address expression"))
3211 return true;
3212
3213 if (Fn.Kind != ValID::t_GlobalID && Fn.Kind != ValID::t_GlobalName)
3214 return Error(Fn.Loc, "expected function name in blockaddress");
3215 if (Label.Kind != ValID::t_LocalID && Label.Kind != ValID::t_LocalName)
3216 return Error(Label.Loc, "expected basic block name in blockaddress");
3217
3218 // Try to find the function (but skip it if it's forward-referenced).
3219 GlobalValue *GV = nullptr;
3220 if (Fn.Kind == ValID::t_GlobalID) {
3221 if (Fn.UIntVal < NumberedVals.size())
3222 GV = NumberedVals[Fn.UIntVal];
3223 } else if (!ForwardRefVals.count(Fn.StrVal)) {
3224 GV = M->getNamedValue(Fn.StrVal);
3225 }
3226 Function *F = nullptr;
3227 if (GV) {
3228 // Confirm that it's actually a function with a definition.
3229 if (!isa<Function>(GV))
3230 return Error(Fn.Loc, "expected function name in blockaddress");
3231 F = cast<Function>(GV);
3232 if (F->isDeclaration())
3233 return Error(Fn.Loc, "cannot take blockaddress inside a declaration");
3234 }
3235
3236 if (!F) {
3237 // Make a global variable as a placeholder for this reference.
3238 GlobalValue *&FwdRef =
3239 ForwardRefBlockAddresses.insert(std::make_pair(
3240 std::move(Fn),
3241 std::map<ValID, GlobalValue *>()))
3242 .first->second.insert(std::make_pair(std::move(Label), nullptr))
3243 .first->second;
3244 if (!FwdRef)
3245 FwdRef = new GlobalVariable(*M, Type::getInt8Ty(Context), false,
3246 GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, nullptr, "");
3247 ID.ConstantVal = FwdRef;
3248 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3249 return false;
3250 }
3251
3252 // We found the function; now find the basic block. Don't use PFS, since we
3253 // might be inside a constant expression.
3254 BasicBlock *BB;
3255 if (BlockAddressPFS && F == &BlockAddressPFS->getFunction()) {
3256 if (Label.Kind == ValID::t_LocalID)
3257 BB = BlockAddressPFS->GetBB(Label.UIntVal, Label.Loc);
3258 else
3259 BB = BlockAddressPFS->GetBB(Label.StrVal, Label.Loc);
3260 if (!BB)
3261 return Error(Label.Loc, "referenced value is not a basic block");
3262 } else {
3263 if (Label.Kind == ValID::t_LocalID)
3264 return Error(Label.Loc, "cannot take address of numeric label after "
3265 "the function is defined");
3266 BB = dyn_cast_or_null<BasicBlock>(
3267 F->getValueSymbolTable()->lookup(Label.StrVal));
3268 if (!BB)
3269 return Error(Label.Loc, "referenced value is not a basic block");
3270 }
3271
3272 ID.ConstantVal = BlockAddress::get(F, BB);
3273 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3274 return false;
3275 }
3276
3277 case lltok::kw_trunc:
3278 case lltok::kw_zext:
3279 case lltok::kw_sext:
3280 case lltok::kw_fptrunc:
3281 case lltok::kw_fpext:
3282 case lltok::kw_bitcast:
3283 case lltok::kw_addrspacecast:
3284 case lltok::kw_uitofp:
3285 case lltok::kw_sitofp:
3286 case lltok::kw_fptoui:
3287 case lltok::kw_fptosi:
3288 case lltok::kw_inttoptr:
3289 case lltok::kw_ptrtoint: {
3290 unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3291 Type *DestTy = nullptr;
3292 Constant *SrcVal;
3293 Lex.Lex();
3294 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' after constantexpr cast") ||
3295 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(SrcVal) ||
3296 ParseToken(lltok::kw_to, "expected 'to' in constantexpr cast") ||
3297 ParseType(DestTy) ||
3298 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' at end of constantexpr cast"))
3299 return true;
3300 if (!CastInst::castIsValid((Instruction::CastOps)Opc, SrcVal, DestTy))
3301 return Error(ID.Loc, "invalid cast opcode for cast from '" +
3302 getTypeString(SrcVal->getType()) + "' to '" +
3303 getTypeString(DestTy) + "'");
3304 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getCast((Instruction::CastOps)Opc,
3305 SrcVal, DestTy);
3306 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3307 return false;
3308 }
3309 case lltok::kw_extractvalue: {
3310 Lex.Lex();
3311 Constant *Val;
3312 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> Indices;
3313 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in extractvalue constantexpr")||
3314 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val) ||
3315 ParseIndexList(Indices) ||
3316 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in extractvalue constantexpr"))
3317 return true;
3318
3319 if (!Val->getType()->isAggregateType())
3320 return Error(ID.Loc, "extractvalue operand must be aggregate type");
3321 if (!ExtractValueInst::getIndexedType(Val->getType(), Indices))
3322 return Error(ID.Loc, "invalid indices for extractvalue");
3323 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getExtractValue(Val, Indices);
3324 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3325 return false;
3326 }
3327 case lltok::kw_insertvalue: {
3328 Lex.Lex();
3329 Constant *Val0, *Val1;
3330 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> Indices;
3331 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in insertvalue constantexpr")||
3332 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val0) ||
3333 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in insertvalue constantexpr")||
3334 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val1) ||
3335 ParseIndexList(Indices) ||
3336 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in insertvalue constantexpr"))
3337 return true;
3338 if (!Val0->getType()->isAggregateType())
3339 return Error(ID.Loc, "insertvalue operand must be aggregate type");
3340 Type *IndexedType =
3341 ExtractValueInst::getIndexedType(Val0->getType(), Indices);
3342 if (!IndexedType)
3343 return Error(ID.Loc, "invalid indices for insertvalue");
3344 if (IndexedType != Val1->getType())
3345 return Error(ID.Loc, "insertvalue operand and field disagree in type: '" +
3346 getTypeString(Val1->getType()) +
3347 "' instead of '" + getTypeString(IndexedType) +
3348 "'");
3349 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getInsertValue(Val0, Val1, Indices);
3350 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3351 return false;
3352 }
3353 case lltok::kw_icmp:
3354 case lltok::kw_fcmp: {
3355 unsigned PredVal, Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3356 Constant *Val0, *Val1;
3357 Lex.Lex();
3358 if (ParseCmpPredicate(PredVal, Opc) ||
3359 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in compare constantexpr") ||
3360 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val0) ||
3361 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in compare constantexpr") ||
3362 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val1) ||
3363 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in compare constantexpr"))
3364 return true;
3365
3366 if (Val0->getType() != Val1->getType())
3367 return Error(ID.Loc, "compare operands must have the same type");
3368
3369 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = (CmpInst::Predicate)PredVal;
3370
3371 if (Opc == Instruction::FCmp) {
3372 if (!Val0->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
3373 return Error(ID.Loc, "fcmp requires floating point operands");
3374 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getFCmp(Pred, Val0, Val1);
3375 } else {
3376 assert(Opc == Instruction::ICmp && "Unexpected opcode for CmpInst!");
3377 if (!Val0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() &&
3378 !Val0->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy())
3379 return Error(ID.Loc, "icmp requires pointer or integer operands");
3380 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getICmp(Pred, Val0, Val1);
3381 }
3382 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3383 return false;
3384 }
3385
3386 // Unary Operators.
3387 case lltok::kw_fneg: {
3388 unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3389 Constant *Val;
3390 Lex.Lex();
3391 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in unary constantexpr") ||
3392 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val) ||
3393 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in unary constantexpr"))
3394 return true;
3395
3396 // Check that the type is valid for the operator.
3397 switch (Opc) {
3398 case Instruction::FNeg:
3399 if (!Val->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
3400 return Error(ID.Loc, "constexpr requires fp operands");
3401 break;
3402 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown unary operator!");
3403 }
3404 unsigned Flags = 0;
3405 Constant *C = ConstantExpr::get(Opc, Val, Flags);
3406 ID.ConstantVal = C;
3407 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3408 return false;
3409 }
3410 // Binary Operators.
3411 case lltok::kw_add:
3412 case lltok::kw_fadd:
3413 case lltok::kw_sub:
3414 case lltok::kw_fsub:
3415 case lltok::kw_mul:
3416 case lltok::kw_fmul:
3417 case lltok::kw_udiv:
3418 case lltok::kw_sdiv:
3419 case lltok::kw_fdiv:
3420 case lltok::kw_urem:
3421 case lltok::kw_srem:
3422 case lltok::kw_frem:
3423 case lltok::kw_shl:
3424 case lltok::kw_lshr:
3425 case lltok::kw_ashr: {
3426 bool NUW = false;
3427 bool NSW = false;
3428 bool Exact = false;
3429 unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3430 Constant *Val0, *Val1;
3431 Lex.Lex();
3432 if (Opc == Instruction::Add || Opc == Instruction::Sub ||
3433 Opc == Instruction::Mul || Opc == Instruction::Shl) {
3434 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nuw))
3435 NUW = true;
3436 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nsw)) {
3437 NSW = true;
3438 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_nuw))
3439 NUW = true;
3440 }
3441 } else if (Opc == Instruction::SDiv || Opc == Instruction::UDiv ||
3442 Opc == Instruction::LShr || Opc == Instruction::AShr) {
3443 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_exact))
3444 Exact = true;
3445 }
3446 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in binary constantexpr") ||
3447 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val0) ||
3448 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in binary constantexpr") ||
3449 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val1) ||
3450 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in binary constantexpr"))
3451 return true;
3452 if (Val0->getType() != Val1->getType())
3453 return Error(ID.Loc, "operands of constexpr must have same type");
3454 // Check that the type is valid for the operator.
3455 switch (Opc) {
3456 case Instruction::Add:
3457 case Instruction::Sub:
3458 case Instruction::Mul:
3459 case Instruction::UDiv:
3460 case Instruction::SDiv:
3461 case Instruction::URem:
3462 case Instruction::SRem:
3463 case Instruction::Shl:
3464 case Instruction::AShr:
3465 case Instruction::LShr:
3466 if (!Val0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
3467 return Error(ID.Loc, "constexpr requires integer operands");
3468 break;
3469 case Instruction::FAdd:
3470 case Instruction::FSub:
3471 case Instruction::FMul:
3472 case Instruction::FDiv:
3473 case Instruction::FRem:
3474 if (!Val0->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
3475 return Error(ID.Loc, "constexpr requires fp operands");
3476 break;
3477 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown binary operator!");
3478 }
3479 unsigned Flags = 0;
3480 if (NUW) Flags |= OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoUnsignedWrap;
3481 if (NSW) Flags |= OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoSignedWrap;
3482 if (Exact) Flags |= PossiblyExactOperator::IsExact;
3483 Constant *C = ConstantExpr::get(Opc, Val0, Val1, Flags);
3484 ID.ConstantVal = C;
3485 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3486 return false;
3487 }
3488
3489 // Logical Operations
3490 case lltok::kw_and:
3491 case lltok::kw_or:
3492 case lltok::kw_xor: {
3493 unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3494 Constant *Val0, *Val1;
3495 Lex.Lex();
3496 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in logical constantexpr") ||
3497 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val0) ||
3498 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in logical constantexpr") ||
3499 ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Val1) ||
3500 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in logical constantexpr"))
3501 return true;
3502 if (Val0->getType() != Val1->getType())
3503 return Error(ID.Loc, "operands of constexpr must have same type");
3504 if (!Val0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
3505 return Error(ID.Loc,
3506 "constexpr requires integer or integer vector operands");
3507 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::get(Opc, Val0, Val1);
3508 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3509 return false;
3510 }
3511
3512 case lltok::kw_getelementptr:
3513 case lltok::kw_shufflevector:
3514 case lltok::kw_insertelement:
3515 case lltok::kw_extractelement:
3516 case lltok::kw_select: {
3517 unsigned Opc = Lex.getUIntVal();
3518 SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
3519 bool InBounds = false;
3520 Type *Ty;
3521 Lex.Lex();
3522
3523 if (Opc == Instruction::GetElementPtr)
3524 InBounds = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_inbounds);
3525
3526 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in constantexpr"))
3527 return true;
3528
3529 LocTy ExplicitTypeLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3530 if (Opc == Instruction::GetElementPtr) {
3531 if (ParseType(Ty) ||
3532 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma after getelementptr's type"))
3533 return true;
3534 }
3535
3536 Optional<unsigned> InRangeOp;
3537 if (ParseGlobalValueVector(
3538 Elts, Opc == Instruction::GetElementPtr ? &InRangeOp : nullptr) ||
3539 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in constantexpr"))
3540 return true;
3541
3542 if (Opc == Instruction::GetElementPtr) {
3543 if (Elts.size() == 0 ||
3544 !Elts[0]->getType()->isPtrOrPtrVectorTy())
3545 return Error(ID.Loc, "base of getelementptr must be a pointer");
3546
3547 Type *BaseType = Elts[0]->getType();
3548 auto *BasePointerType = cast<PointerType>(BaseType->getScalarType());
3549 if (Ty != BasePointerType->getElementType())
3550 return Error(
3551 ExplicitTypeLoc,
3552 "explicit pointee type doesn't match operand's pointee type");
3553
3554 unsigned GEPWidth =
3555 BaseType->isVectorTy() ? BaseType->getVectorNumElements() : 0;
3556
3557 ArrayRef<Constant *> Indices(Elts.begin() + 1, Elts.end());
3558 for (Constant *Val : Indices) {
3559 Type *ValTy = Val->getType();
3560 if (!ValTy->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
3561 return Error(ID.Loc, "getelementptr index must be an integer");
3562 if (ValTy->isVectorTy()) {
3563 unsigned ValNumEl = ValTy->getVectorNumElements();
3564 if (GEPWidth && (ValNumEl != GEPWidth))
3565 return Error(
3566 ID.Loc,
3567 "getelementptr vector index has a wrong number of elements");
3568 // GEPWidth may have been unknown because the base is a scalar,
3569 // but it is known now.
3570 GEPWidth = ValNumEl;
3571 }
3572 }
3573
3574 SmallPtrSet<Type*, 4> Visited;
3575 if (!Indices.empty() && !Ty->isSized(&Visited))
3576 return Error(ID.Loc, "base element of getelementptr must be sized");
3577
3578 if (!GetElementPtrInst::getIndexedType(Ty, Indices))
3579 return Error(ID.Loc, "invalid getelementptr indices");
3580
3581 if (InRangeOp) {
3582 if (*InRangeOp == 0)
3583 return Error(ID.Loc,
3584 "inrange keyword may not appear on pointer operand");
3585 --*InRangeOp;
3586 }
3587
3588 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(Ty, Elts[0], Indices,
3589 InBounds, InRangeOp);
3590 } else if (Opc == Instruction::Select) {
3591 if (Elts.size() != 3)
3592 return Error(ID.Loc, "expected three operands to select");
3593 if (const char *Reason = SelectInst::areInvalidOperands(Elts[0], Elts[1],
3594 Elts[2]))
3595 return Error(ID.Loc, Reason);
3596 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getSelect(Elts[0], Elts[1], Elts[2]);
3597 } else if (Opc == Instruction::ShuffleVector) {
3598 if (Elts.size() != 3)
3599 return Error(ID.Loc, "expected three operands to shufflevector");
3600 if (!ShuffleVectorInst::isValidOperands(Elts[0], Elts[1], Elts[2]))
3601 return Error(ID.Loc, "invalid operands to shufflevector");
3602 ID.ConstantVal =
3603 ConstantExpr::getShuffleVector(Elts[0], Elts[1],Elts[2]);
3604 } else if (Opc == Instruction::ExtractElement) {
3605 if (Elts.size() != 2)
3606 return Error(ID.Loc, "expected two operands to extractelement");
3607 if (!ExtractElementInst::isValidOperands(Elts[0], Elts[1]))
3608 return Error(ID.Loc, "invalid extractelement operands");
3609 ID.ConstantVal = ConstantExpr::getExtractElement(Elts[0], Elts[1]);
3610 } else {
3611 assert(Opc == Instruction::InsertElement && "Unknown opcode");
3612 if (Elts.size() != 3)
3613 return Error(ID.Loc, "expected three operands to insertelement");
3614 if (!InsertElementInst::isValidOperands(Elts[0], Elts[1], Elts[2]))
3615 return Error(ID.Loc, "invalid insertelement operands");
3616 ID.ConstantVal =
3617 ConstantExpr::getInsertElement(Elts[0], Elts[1],Elts[2]);
3618 }
3619
3620 ID.Kind = ValID::t_Constant;
3621 return false;
3622 }
3623 }
3624
3625 Lex.Lex();
3626 return false;
3627}
3628
3629/// ParseGlobalValue - Parse a global value with the specified type.
3630bool LLParser::ParseGlobalValue(Type *Ty, Constant *&C) {
3631 C = nullptr;
3632 ValID ID;
3633 Value *V = nullptr;
3634 bool Parsed = ParseValID(ID) ||
3635 ConvertValIDToValue(Ty, ID, V, nullptr, /*IsCall=*/false);
3636 if (V && !(C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V)))
3637 return Error(ID.Loc, "global values must be constants");
3638 return Parsed;
3639}
3640
3641bool LLParser::ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(Constant *&V) {
3642 Type *Ty = nullptr;
3643 return ParseType(Ty) ||
3644 ParseGlobalValue(Ty, V);
3645}
3646
3647bool LLParser::parseOptionalComdat(StringRef GlobalName, Comdat *&C) {
3648 C = nullptr;
3649
3650 LocTy KwLoc = Lex.getLoc();
3651 if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_comdat))
3652 return false;
3653
3654 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::lparen)) {
3655 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::ComdatVar)
3656 return TokError("expected comdat variable");
3657 C = getComdat(Lex.getStrVal(), Lex.getLoc());
3658 Lex.Lex();
3659 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' after comdat var"))
3660 return true;
3661 } else {
3662 if (GlobalName.empty())
3663 return TokError("comdat cannot be unnamed");
3664 C = getComdat(GlobalName, KwLoc);
3665 }
3666
3667 return false;
3668}
3669
3670/// ParseGlobalValueVector
3671/// ::= /*empty*/
3672/// ::= [inrange] TypeAndValue (',' [inrange] TypeAndValue)*
3673bool LLParser::ParseGlobalValueVector(SmallVectorImpl<Constant *> &Elts,
3674 Optional<unsigned> *InRangeOp) {
3675 // Empty list.
3676 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::rbrace ||
3677 Lex.getKind() == lltok::rsquare ||
3678 Lex.getKind() == lltok::greater ||
3679 Lex.getKind() == lltok::rparen)
3680 return false;
3681
3682 do {
3683 if (InRangeOp && !*InRangeOp && EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_inrange))
3684 *InRangeOp = Elts.size();
3685
3686 Constant *C;
3687 if (ParseGlobalTypeAndValue(C)) return true;
3688 Elts.push_back(C);
3689 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
3690
3691 return false;
3692}
3693
3694bool LLParser::ParseMDTuple(MDNode *&MD, bool IsDistinct) {
3695 SmallVector<Metadata *, 16> Elts;
3696 if (ParseMDNodeVector(Elts))
3697 return true;
3698
3699 MD = (IsDistinct ? MDTuple::getDistinct : MDTuple::get)(Context, Elts);
3700 return false;
3701}
3702
3703/// MDNode:
3704/// ::= !{ ... }
3705/// ::= !7
3706/// ::= !DILocation(...)
3707bool LLParser::ParseMDNode(MDNode *&N) {
3708 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar)
3709 return ParseSpecializedMDNode(N);
3710
3711 return ParseToken(lltok::exclaim, "expected '!' here") ||
3712 ParseMDNodeTail(N);
3713}
3714
3715bool LLParser::ParseMDNodeTail(MDNode *&N) {
3716 // !{ ... }
3717 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::lbrace)
3718 return ParseMDTuple(N);
3719
3720 // !42
3721 return ParseMDNodeID(N);
3722}

3726/// Structure to represent an optional metadata field.
3727template <class FieldTy> struct MDFieldImpl {
3728 typedef MDFieldImpl ImplTy;
3729 FieldTy Val;
3730 bool Seen;
3731
3732 void assign(FieldTy Val) {
3733 Seen = true;
3734 this->Val = std::move(Val);
3735 }
3736
3737 explicit MDFieldImpl(FieldTy Default)
3738 : Val(std::move(Default)), Seen(false) {}
3739};
3740
3741/// Structure to represent an optional metadata field that
3742/// can be of either type (A or B) and encapsulates the
3743/// MD<typeofA>Field and MD<typeofB>Field structs, so not
3744/// to reimplement the specifics for representing each Field.
3745template <class FieldTypeA, class FieldTypeB> struct MDEitherFieldImpl {
3746 typedef MDEitherFieldImpl<FieldTypeA, FieldTypeB> ImplTy;
3747 FieldTypeA A;
3748 FieldTypeB B;
3749 bool Seen;
3750
3751 enum {
3752 IsInvalid = 0,
3753 IsTypeA = 1,
3754 IsTypeB = 2
3755 } WhatIs;
3756
3757 void assign(FieldTypeA A) {
3758 Seen = true;
3759 this->A = std::move(A);
3760 WhatIs = IsTypeA;
3761 }
3762
3763 void assign(FieldTypeB B) {
3764 Seen = true;
3765 this->B = std::move(B);
3766 WhatIs = IsTypeB;
3767 }
3768
3769 explicit MDEitherFieldImpl(FieldTypeA DefaultA, FieldTypeB DefaultB)
3770 : A(std::move(DefaultA)), B(std::move(DefaultB)), Seen(false),
3771 WhatIs(IsInvalid) {}
3772};
3773
3774struct MDUnsignedField : public MDFieldImpl<uint64_t> {
3775 uint64_t Max;
3776
3777 MDUnsignedField(uint64_t Default = 0, uint64_t Max = UINT64_MAX)
3778 : ImplTy(Default), Max(Max) {}
3779};

3870struct ChecksumKindField : public MDFieldImpl<DIFile::ChecksumKind> {
3871 ChecksumKindField(DIFile::ChecksumKind CSKind) : ImplTy(CSKind) {}
3872};

3874struct MDSignedOrMDField : MDEitherFieldImpl<MDSignedField, MDField> {
3875 MDSignedOrMDField(int64_t Default = 0, bool AllowNull = true)
3876 : ImplTy(MDSignedField(Default), MDField(AllowNull)) {}
3877
3878 MDSignedOrMDField(int64_t Default, int64_t Min, int64_t Max,
3879 bool AllowNull = true)
3880 : ImplTy(MDSignedField(Default, Min, Max), MDField(AllowNull)) {}
3881
3882 bool isMDSignedField() const { return WhatIs == IsTypeA; }
3883 bool isMDField() const { return WhatIs == IsTypeB; }
3884 int64_t getMDSignedValue() const {
3885 assert(isMDSignedField() && "Wrong field type");
3886 return A.Val;
3887 }
3888 Metadata *getMDFieldValue() const {
3889 assert(isMDField() && "Wrong field type");
3890 return B.Val;
3891 }
3892};

3894struct MDSignedOrUnsignedField
3895 : MDEitherFieldImpl<MDSignedField, MDUnsignedField> {
3896 MDSignedOrUnsignedField() : ImplTy(MDSignedField(0), MDUnsignedField(0)) {}
3897
3898 bool isMDSignedField() const { return WhatIs == IsTypeA; }
3899 bool isMDUnsignedField() const { return WhatIs == IsTypeB; }
3900 int64_t getMDSignedValue() const {
3901 assert(isMDSignedField() && "Wrong field type");
3902 return A.Val;
3903 }
3904 uint64_t getMDUnsignedValue() const {
3905 assert(isMDUnsignedField() && "Wrong field type");
3906 return B.Val;
3907 }
3908};

4088/// DIFlagField
4089/// ::= uint32
4090/// ::= DIFlagVector
4091/// ::= DIFlagVector '|' DIFlagFwdDecl '|' uint32 '|' DIFlagPublic
4092template <>
4093bool LLParser::ParseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name, DIFlagField &Result) {
4094
4095 // Parser for a single flag.
4096 auto parseFlag = [&](DINode::DIFlags &Val) {
4097 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::APSInt && !Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned()) {
4098 uint32_t TempVal = static_cast<uint32_t>(Val);
4099 bool Res = ParseUInt32(TempVal);
4100 Val = static_cast<DINode::DIFlags>(TempVal);
4101 return Res;
4102 }
4103
4104 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::DIFlag)
4105 return TokError("expected debug info flag");
4106
4107 Val = DINode::getFlag(Lex.getStrVal());
4108 if (!Val)
4109 return TokError(Twine("invalid debug info flag flag '") +
4110 Lex.getStrVal() + "'");
4111 Lex.Lex();
4112 return false;
4113 };
4114
4115 // Parse the flags and combine them together.
4116 DINode::DIFlags Combined = DINode::FlagZero;
4117 do {
4118 DINode::DIFlags Val;
4119 if (parseFlag(Val))
4120 return true;
4121 Combined |= Val;
4122 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::bar));
4123
4124 Result.assign(Combined);
4125 return false;
4126}
4127
4128/// DISPFlagField
4129/// ::= uint32
4130/// ::= DISPFlagVector
4131/// ::= DISPFlagVector '|' DISPFlag* '|' uint32
4132template <>
4133bool LLParser::ParseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name, DISPFlagField &Result) {
4134
4135 // Parser for a single flag.
4136 auto parseFlag = [&](DISubprogram::DISPFlags &Val) {
4137 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::APSInt && !Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned()) {
4138 uint32_t TempVal = static_cast<uint32_t>(Val);
4139 bool Res = ParseUInt32(TempVal);
4140 Val = static_cast<DISubprogram::DISPFlags>(TempVal);
4141 return Res;
4142 }
4143
4144 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::DISPFlag)
4145 return TokError("expected debug info flag");
4146
4147 Val = DISubprogram::getFlag(Lex.getStrVal());
4148 if (!Val)
4149 return TokError(Twine("invalid subprogram debug info flag '") +
4150 Lex.getStrVal() + "'");
4151 Lex.Lex();
4152 return false;
4153 };
4154
4155 // Parse the flags and combine them together.
4156 DISubprogram::DISPFlags Combined = DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
4157 do {
4158 DISubprogram::DISPFlags Val;
4159 if (parseFlag(Val))
4160 return true;
4161 Combined |= Val;
4162 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::bar));
4163
4164 Result.assign(Combined);
4165 return false;
4166}

4168template <>
4169bool LLParser::ParseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name,
4170 MDSignedField &Result) {
4171 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt)
4172 return TokError("expected signed integer");
4173
4174 auto &S = Lex.getAPSIntVal();
4175 if (S < Result.Min)
4176 return TokError("value for '" + Name + "' too small, limit is " +
4177 Twine(Result.Min));
4178 if (S > Result.Max)
4179 return TokError("value for '" + Name + "' too large, limit is " +
4180 Twine(Result.Max));
4181 Result.assign(S.getExtValue());
4182 assert(Result.Val >= Result.Min && "Expected value in range");
4183 assert(Result.Val <= Result.Max && "Expected value in range");
4184 Lex.Lex();
4185 return false;
4186}

4188template <>
4189bool LLParser::ParseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name, MDBoolField &Result) {
4190 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
4191 default:
4192 return TokError("expected 'true' or 'false'");
4193 case lltok::kw_true:
4194 Result.assign(true);
4195 break;
4196 case lltok::kw_false:
4197 Result.assign(false);
4198 break;
4199 }
4200 Lex.Lex();
4201 return false;
4202}

4204template <>
4205bool LLParser::ParseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name, MDField &Result) {
4206 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_null) {
4207 if (!Result.AllowNull)
4208 return TokError("'" + Name + "' cannot be null");
4209 Lex.Lex();
4210 Result.assign(nullptr);
4211 return false;
4212 }
4213
4214 Metadata *MD;
4215 if (ParseMetadata(MD, nullptr))
4216 return true;
4217
4218 Result.assign(MD);
4219 return false;
4220}

4222template <>
4223bool LLParser::ParseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name,
4224 MDSignedOrMDField &Result) {
4225 // Try to parse a signed int.
4226 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::APSInt) {
4227 MDSignedField Res = Result.A;
4228 if (!ParseMDField(Loc, Name, Res)) {
4229 Result.assign(Res);
4230 return false;
4231 }
4232 return true;
4233 }
4234
4235 // Otherwise, try to parse as an MDField.
4236 MDField Res = Result.B;
4237 if (!ParseMDField(Loc, Name, Res)) {
4238 Result.assign(Res);
4239 return false;
4240 }
4241
4242 return true;
4243}
4244
4245template <>
4246bool LLParser::ParseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name,
4247 MDSignedOrUnsignedField &Result) {
4248 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt)
4249 return false;
4250
4251 if (Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned()) {
4252 MDSignedField Res = Result.A;
4253 if (ParseMDField(Loc, Name, Res))
4254 return true;
4255 Result.assign(Res);
4256 return false;
4257 }
4258
4259 MDUnsignedField Res = Result.B;
4260 if (ParseMDField(Loc, Name, Res))
4261 return true;
4262 Result.assign(Res);
4263 return false;
4264}

4266template <>
4267bool LLParser::ParseMDField(LocTy Loc, StringRef Name, MDStringField &Result) {
4268 LocTy ValueLoc = Lex.getLoc();
4269 std::string S;
4270 if (ParseStringConstant(S))
4271 return true;
4272
4273 if (!Result.AllowEmpty && S.empty())
4274 return Error(ValueLoc, "'" + Name + "' cannot be empty");
4275
4276 Result.assign(S.empty() ? nullptr : MDString::get(Context, S));
4277 return false;
4278}

4307template <class ParserTy>
4308bool LLParser::ParseMDFieldsImplBody(ParserTy parseField) {
4309 do {
4310 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::LabelStr)
4311 return TokError("expected field label here");
4312
4313 if (parseField())
4314 return true;
4315 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
4316
4317 return false;
4318}

4320template <class ParserTy>
4321bool LLParser::ParseMDFieldsImpl(ParserTy parseField, LocTy &ClosingLoc) {
4322 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar && "Expected metadata type name");
4323 Lex.Lex();
4324
4325 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
4326 return true;
4327 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rparen)
4328 if (ParseMDFieldsImplBody(parseField))
4329 return true;
4330
4331 ClosingLoc = Lex.getLoc();
4332 return ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here");
4333}

4335template <class FieldTy>
4336bool LLParser::ParseMDField(StringRef Name, FieldTy &Result) {
4337 if (Result.Seen)
4338 return TokError("field '" + Name + "' cannot be specified more than once");
4339
4340 LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
4341 Lex.Lex();
4342 return ParseMDField(Loc, Name, Result);
4343}
4344
4345bool LLParser::ParseSpecializedMDNode(MDNode *&N, bool IsDistinct) {
4346 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar && "Expected metadata type name");
4347
4348#define HANDLE_SPECIALIZED_MDNODE_LEAF(CLASS) \
4349 if (Lex.getStrVal() == #CLASS) \
4350 return Parse##CLASS(N, IsDistinct);
4351#include "llvm/IR/Metadata.def"
4352
4353 return TokError("expected metadata type");
4354}
4355
4356#define DECLARE_FIELD(NAME, TYPE, INIT) TYPE NAME INIT
4357#define NOP_FIELD(NAME, TYPE, INIT)
4358#define REQUIRE_FIELD(NAME, TYPE, INIT) \
4359 if (!NAME.Seen) \
4360 return Error(ClosingLoc, "missing required field '" #NAME "'");
4361#define PARSE_MD_FIELD(NAME, TYPE, DEFAULT) \
4362 if (Lex.getStrVal() == #NAME) \
4363 return ParseMDField(#NAME, NAME);
4364#define PARSE_MD_FIELDS() \
4365 VISIT_MD_FIELDS(DECLARE_FIELD, DECLARE_FIELD) \
4366 do { \
4367 LocTy ClosingLoc; \
4368 if (ParseMDFieldsImpl([&]() -> bool { \
4369 VISIT_MD_FIELDS(PARSE_MD_FIELD, PARSE_MD_FIELD) \
4370 return TokError(Twine("invalid field '") + Lex.getStrVal() + "'"); \
4371 }, ClosingLoc)) \
4372 return true; \
4373 VISIT_MD_FIELDS(NOP_FIELD, REQUIRE_FIELD) \
4374 } while (false)
4375#define GET_OR_DISTINCT(CLASS, ARGS) \
4376 (IsDistinct ? CLASS::getDistinct ARGS : CLASS::get ARGS)
4377
4378/// ParseDILocationFields:
4379/// ::= !DILocation(line: 43, column: 8, scope: !5, inlinedAt: !6,
4380/// isImplicitCode: true)
4381bool LLParser::ParseDILocation(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4382#define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4383 OPTIONAL(line, LineField, ); \
4384 OPTIONAL(column, ColumnField, ); \
4385 REQUIRED(scope, MDField, (/* AllowNull */ false)); \
4386 OPTIONAL(inlinedAt, MDField, ); \
4387 OPTIONAL(isImplicitCode, MDBoolField, (false));
4388 PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4389#undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4390
4391 Result =
4392 GET_OR_DISTINCT(DILocation, (Context, line.Val, column.Val, scope.Val,
4393 inlinedAt.Val, isImplicitCode.Val));
4394 return false;
4395}

4397/// ParseGenericDINode:
4398/// ::= !GenericDINode(tag: 15, header: "...", operands: {...})
4399bool LLParser::ParseGenericDINode(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4400#define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4401 REQUIRED(tag, DwarfTagField, ); \
4402 OPTIONAL(header, MDStringField, ); \
4403 OPTIONAL(operands, MDFieldList, );
4404 PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4405#undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4406
4407 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(GenericDINode,
4408 (Context, tag.Val, header.Val, operands.Val));
4409 return false;
4410}

4412/// ParseDISubrange:
4413/// ::= !DISubrange(count: 30, lowerBound: 2)
4414/// ::= !DISubrange(count: !node, lowerBound: 2)
4415bool LLParser::ParseDISubrange(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4416#define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4417 REQUIRED(count, MDSignedOrMDField, (-1, -1, INT64_MAX, false)); \
4418 OPTIONAL(lowerBound, MDSignedField, );
4419 PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4420#undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4421
4422 if (count.isMDSignedField())
4423 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(
4424 DISubrange, (Context, count.getMDSignedValue(), lowerBound.Val));
4425 else if (count.isMDField())
4426 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(
4427 DISubrange, (Context, count.getMDFieldValue(), lowerBound.Val));
4428 else
4429 return true;
4430
4431 return false;
4432}

4434/// ParseDIEnumerator:
4435/// ::= !DIEnumerator(value: 30, isUnsigned: true, name: "SomeKind")
4436bool LLParser::ParseDIEnumerator(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4437#define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4438 REQUIRED(name, MDStringField, ); \
4439 REQUIRED(value, MDSignedOrUnsignedField, ); \
4440 OPTIONAL(isUnsigned, MDBoolField, (false));
4441 PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4442#undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4443
4444 if (isUnsigned.Val && value.isMDSignedField())
4445 return TokError("unsigned enumerator with negative value");
4446
4447 int64_t Value = value.isMDSignedField()
4448 ? value.getMDSignedValue()
4449 : static_cast<int64_t>(value.getMDUnsignedValue());
4450 Result =
4451 GET_OR_DISTINCT(DIEnumerator, (Context, Value, isUnsigned.Val, name.Val));
4452
4453 return false;
4454}

4475/// ParseDIDerivedType:
4476/// ::= !DIDerivedType(tag: DW_TAG_pointer_type, name: "int", file: !0,
4477/// line: 7, scope: !1, baseType: !2, size: 32,
4478/// align: 32, offset: 0, flags: 0, extraData: !3,
4479/// dwarfAddressSpace: 3)
4480bool LLParser::ParseDIDerivedType(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4481#define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4482 REQUIRED(tag, DwarfTagField, ); \
4483 OPTIONAL(name, MDStringField, ); \
4484 OPTIONAL(file, MDField, ); \
4485 OPTIONAL(line, LineField, ); \
4486 OPTIONAL(scope, MDField, ); \
4487 REQUIRED(baseType, MDField, ); \
4488 OPTIONAL(size, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT64_MAX)); \
4489 OPTIONAL(align, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT32_MAX)); \
4490 OPTIONAL(offset, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT64_MAX)); \
4491 OPTIONAL(flags, DIFlagField, ); \
4492 OPTIONAL(extraData, MDField, ); \
4493 OPTIONAL(dwarfAddressSpace, MDUnsignedField, (UINT32_MAX, UINT32_MAX));
4494 PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4495#undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4496
4497 Optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace;
4498 if (dwarfAddressSpace.Val != UINT32_MAX)
4499 DWARFAddressSpace = dwarfAddressSpace.Val;
4500
4501 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(DIDerivedType,
4502 (Context, tag.Val, name.Val, file.Val, line.Val,
4503 scope.Val, baseType.Val, size.Val, align.Val,
4504 offset.Val, DWARFAddressSpace, flags.Val,
4505 extraData.Val));
4506 return false;
4507}
4508
4509bool LLParser::ParseDICompositeType(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4510#define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4511 REQUIRED(tag, DwarfTagField, ); \
4512 OPTIONAL(name, MDStringField, ); \
4513 OPTIONAL(file, MDField, ); \
4514 OPTIONAL(line, LineField, ); \
4515 OPTIONAL(scope, MDField, ); \
4516 OPTIONAL(baseType, MDField, ); \
4517 OPTIONAL(size, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT64_MAX)); \
4518 OPTIONAL(align, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT32_MAX)); \
4519 OPTIONAL(offset, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT64_MAX)); \
4520 OPTIONAL(flags, DIFlagField, ); \
4521 OPTIONAL(elements, MDField, ); \
4522 OPTIONAL(runtimeLang, DwarfLangField, ); \
4523 OPTIONAL(vtableHolder, MDField, ); \
4524 OPTIONAL(templateParams, MDField, ); \
4525 OPTIONAL(identifier, MDStringField, ); \
4526 OPTIONAL(discriminator, MDField, );
4527 PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4528#undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4529
4530 // If this has an identifier try to build an ODR type.
4531 if (identifier.Val)
4532 if (auto *CT = DICompositeType::buildODRType(
4533 Context, *identifier.Val, tag.Val, name.Val, file.Val, line.Val,
4534 scope.Val, baseType.Val, size.Val, align.Val, offset.Val, flags.Val,
4535 elements.Val, runtimeLang.Val, vtableHolder.Val,
4536 templateParams.Val, discriminator.Val)) {
4537 Result = CT;
4538 return false;
4539 }
4540
4541 // Create a new node, and save it in the context if it belongs in the type
4542 // map.
4543 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(
4544 DICompositeType,
4545 (Context, tag.Val, name.Val, file.Val, line.Val, scope.Val, baseType.Val,
4546 size.Val, align.Val, offset.Val, flags.Val, elements.Val,
4547 runtimeLang.Val, vtableHolder.Val, templateParams.Val, identifier.Val,
4548 discriminator.Val));
4549 return false;
4550}

4565/// ParseDIFileType:
4566/// ::= !DIFileType(filename: "path/to/file", directory: "/path/to/dir",
4567/// checksumkind: CSK_MD5,
4568/// checksum: "000102030405060708090a0b0c0d0e0f",
4569/// source: "source file contents")
4570bool LLParser::ParseDIFile(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4571 // The default constructed value for checksumkind is required, but will never
4572 // be used, as the parser checks if the field was actually Seen before using
4573 // the Val.
4574#define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4575 REQUIRED(filename, MDStringField, ); \
4576 REQUIRED(directory, MDStringField, ); \
4577 OPTIONAL(checksumkind, ChecksumKindField, (DIFile::CSK_MD5)); \
4578 OPTIONAL(checksum, MDStringField, ); \
4579 OPTIONAL(source, MDStringField, );
4580 PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4581#undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4582
4583 Optional<DIFile::ChecksumInfo<MDString *>> OptChecksum;
4584 if (checksumkind.Seen && checksum.Seen)
4585 OptChecksum.emplace(checksumkind.Val, checksum.Val);
4586 else if (checksumkind.Seen || checksum.Seen)
4587 return Lex.Error("'checksumkind' and 'checksum' must be provided together");
4588
4589 Optional<MDString *> OptSource;
4590 if (source.Seen)
4591 OptSource = source.Val;
4592 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(DIFile, (Context, filename.Val, directory.Val,
4593 OptChecksum, OptSource));
4594 return false;
4595}

4638/// ParseDISubprogram:
4639/// ::= !DISubprogram(scope: !0, name: "foo", linkageName: "_Zfoo",
4640/// file: !1, line: 7, type: !2, isLocal: false,
4641/// isDefinition: true, scopeLine: 8, containingType: !3,
4642/// virtuality: DW_VIRTUALTIY_pure_virtual,
4643/// virtualIndex: 10, thisAdjustment: 4, flags: 11,
4644/// spFlags: 10, isOptimized: false, templateParams: !4,
4645/// declaration: !5, retainedNodes: !6, thrownTypes: !7)
4646bool LLParser::ParseDISubprogram(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4647 auto Loc = Lex.getLoc();
4648#define VISIT_MD_FIELDS(OPTIONAL, REQUIRED) \
4649 OPTIONAL(scope, MDField, ); \
4650 OPTIONAL(name, MDStringField, ); \
4651 OPTIONAL(linkageName, MDStringField, ); \
4652 OPTIONAL(file, MDField, ); \
4653 OPTIONAL(line, LineField, ); \
4654 OPTIONAL(type, MDField, ); \
4655 OPTIONAL(isLocal, MDBoolField, ); \
4656 OPTIONAL(isDefinition, MDBoolField, (true)); \
4657 OPTIONAL(scopeLine, LineField, ); \
4658 OPTIONAL(containingType, MDField, ); \
4659 OPTIONAL(virtuality, DwarfVirtualityField, ); \
4660 OPTIONAL(virtualIndex, MDUnsignedField, (0, UINT32_MAX)); \
4661 OPTIONAL(thisAdjustment, MDSignedField, (0, INT32_MIN, INT32_MAX)); \
4662 OPTIONAL(flags, DIFlagField, ); \
4663 OPTIONAL(spFlags, DISPFlagField, ); \
4664 OPTIONAL(isOptimized, MDBoolField, ); \
4665 OPTIONAL(unit, MDField, ); \
4666 OPTIONAL(templateParams, MDField, ); \
4667 OPTIONAL(declaration, MDField, ); \
4668 OPTIONAL(retainedNodes, MDField, ); \
4669 OPTIONAL(thrownTypes, MDField, );
4670 PARSE_MD_FIELDS();
4671#undef VISIT_MD_FIELDS
4672
4673 // An explicit spFlags field takes precedence over individual fields in
4674 // older IR versions.
4675 DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags =
4676 spFlags.Seen ? spFlags.Val
4677 : DISubprogram::toSPFlags(isLocal.Val, isDefinition.Val,
4678 isOptimized.Val, virtuality.Val);
4679 if ((SPFlags & DISubprogram::SPFlagDefinition) && !IsDistinct)
4680 return Lex.Error(
4681 Loc,
4682 "missing 'distinct', required for !DISubprogram that is a Definition");
4683 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(
4684 DISubprogram,
4685 (Context, scope.Val, name.Val, linkageName.Val, file.Val, line.Val,
4686 type.Val, scopeLine.Val, containingType.Val, virtualIndex.Val,
4687 thisAdjustment.Val, flags.Val, SPFlags, unit.Val, templateParams.Val,
4688 declaration.Val, retainedNodes.Val, thrownTypes.Val));
4689 return false;
4690}

4907
4908/// ParseDIExpression:
4909/// ::= !DIExpression(0, 7, -1)
4910bool LLParser::ParseDIExpression(MDNode *&Result, bool IsDistinct) {
4911 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar && "Expected metadata type name");
4912 Lex.Lex();
4913
4914 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
4915 return true;
4916
4917 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Elements;
4918 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::rparen)
4919 do {
4920 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::DwarfOp) {
4921 if (unsigned Op = dwarf::getOperationEncoding(Lex.getStrVal())) {
4922 Lex.Lex();
4923 Elements.push_back(Op);
4924 continue;
4925 }
4926 return TokError(Twine("invalid DWARF op '") + Lex.getStrVal() + "'");
4927 }
4928
4929 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::DwarfAttEncoding) {
4930 if (unsigned Op = dwarf::getAttributeEncoding(Lex.getStrVal())) {
4931 Lex.Lex();
4932 Elements.push_back(Op);
4933 continue;
4934 }
4935 return TokError(Twine("invalid DWARF attribute encoding '") + Lex.getStrVal() + "'");
4936 }
4937
4938 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt || Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned())
4939 return TokError("expected unsigned integer");
4940
4941 auto &U = Lex.getAPSIntVal();
4942 if (U.ugt(UINT64_MAX))
4943 return TokError("element too large, limit is " + Twine(UINT64_MAX));
4944 Elements.push_back(U.getZExtValue());
4945 Lex.Lex();
4946 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
4947
4948 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
4949 return true;
4950
4951 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(DIExpression, (Context, Elements));
4952 return false;
4953}

5005 Result = GET_OR_DISTINCT(
5006 DIImportedEntity,
5007 (Context, tag.Val, scope.Val, entity.Val, file.Val, line.Val, name.Val));
5008 return false;
5009}
5010
5011#undef PARSE_MD_FIELD
5012#undef NOP_FIELD
5013#undef REQUIRE_FIELD
5014#undef DECLARE_FIELD
5015
5016/// ParseMetadataAsValue
5017/// ::= metadata i32 %local
5018/// ::= metadata i32 @global
5019/// ::= metadata i32 7
5020/// ::= metadata !0
5021/// ::= metadata !{...}
5022/// ::= metadata !"string"
5023bool LLParser::ParseMetadataAsValue(Value *&V, PerFunctionState &PFS) {
5024 // Note: the type 'metadata' has already been parsed.
5025 Metadata *MD;
5026 if (ParseMetadata(MD, &PFS))
5027 return true;
5028
5029 V = MetadataAsValue::get(Context, MD);
5030 return false;
5031}
5032
5033/// ParseValueAsMetadata
5034/// ::= i32 %local
5035/// ::= i32 @global
5036/// ::= i32 7
5037bool LLParser::ParseValueAsMetadata(Metadata *&MD, const Twine &TypeMsg,
5038 PerFunctionState *PFS) {
5039 Type *Ty;
5040 LocTy Loc;
5041 if (ParseType(Ty, TypeMsg, Loc))
5042 return true;
5043 if (Ty->isMetadataTy())
5044 return Error(Loc, "invalid metadata-value-metadata roundtrip");
5045
5046 Value *V;
5047 if (ParseValue(Ty, V, PFS))
5048 return true;
5049
5050 MD = ValueAsMetadata::get(V);
5051 return false;
5052}
5053
5054/// ParseMetadata
5055/// ::= i32 %local
5056/// ::= i32 @global
5057/// ::= i32 7
5058/// ::= !42
5059/// ::= !{...}
5060/// ::= !"string"
5061/// ::= !DILocation(...)
5062bool LLParser::ParseMetadata(Metadata *&MD, PerFunctionState *PFS) {
5063 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::MetadataVar) {
5064 MDNode *N;
5065 if (ParseSpecializedMDNode(N))
5066 return true;
5067 MD = N;
5068 return false;
5069 }
5070
5071 // ValueAsMetadata:
5072 // <type> <value>
5073 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::exclaim)
5074 return ParseValueAsMetadata(MD, "expected metadata operand", PFS);
5075
5076 // '!'.
5077 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::exclaim && "Expected '!' here");
5078 Lex.Lex();
5079
5080 // MDString:
5081 // ::= '!' STRINGCONSTANT
5082 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::StringConstant) {
5083 MDString *S;
5084 if (ParseMDString(S))
5085 return true;
5086 MD = S;
5087 return false;
5088 }
5089
5090 // MDNode:
5091 // !{ ... }
5092 // !7
5093 MDNode *N;
5094 if (ParseMDNodeTail(N))
5095 return true;
5096 MD = N;
5097 return false;
5098}
