7251//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7252// Embedded metadata.
7253//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7254
7255/// ParseMDNodeVector
7256/// ::= { Element (',' Element)* }
7257/// Element
7258/// ::= 'null' | TypeAndValue
7259bool LLParser::ParseMDNodeVector(SmallVectorImpl<Metadata *> &Elts) {
7260 if (ParseToken(lltok::lbrace, "expected '{' here"))
7261 return true;
7262
7263 // Check for an empty list.
7264 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::rbrace))
7265 return false;
7266
7267 do {
7268 // Null is a special case since it is typeless.
7269 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_null)) {
7270 Elts.push_back(nullptr);
7271 continue;
7272 }
7273
7274 Metadata *MD;
7275 if (ParseMetadata(MD, nullptr))
7276 return true;
7277 Elts.push_back(MD);
7278 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
7279
7280 return ParseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected end of metadata node");
7281}
7282
7283//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7284// Use-list order directives.
7285//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7286bool LLParser::sortUseListOrder(Value *V, ArrayRef<unsigned> Indexes,
7287 SMLoc Loc) {
7288 if (V->use_empty())
7289 return Error(Loc, "value has no uses");
7290
7291 unsigned NumUses = 0;
7292 SmallDenseMap<const Use *, unsigned, 16> Order;
7293 for (const Use &U : V->uses()) {
7294 if (++NumUses > Indexes.size())
7295 break;
7296 Order[&U] = Indexes[NumUses - 1];
7297 }
7298 if (NumUses < 2)
7299 return Error(Loc, "value only has one use");
7300 if (Order.size() != Indexes.size() || NumUses > Indexes.size())
7301 return Error(Loc,
7302 "wrong number of indexes, expected " + Twine(V->getNumUses()));
7303
7304 V->sortUseList([&](const Use &L, const Use &R) {
7305 return Order.lookup(&L) < Order.lookup(&R);
7306 });
7307 return false;
7308}
7309
7310/// ParseUseListOrderIndexes
7311/// ::= '{' uint32 (',' uint32)+ '}'
7312bool LLParser::ParseUseListOrderIndexes(SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &Indexes) {
7313 SMLoc Loc = Lex.getLoc();
7314 if (ParseToken(lltok::lbrace, "expected '{' here"))
7315 return true;
7316 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::rbrace)
7317 return Lex.Error("expected non-empty list of uselistorder indexes");
7318
7319 // Use Offset, Max, and IsOrdered to check consistency of indexes. The
7320 // indexes should be distinct numbers in the range [0, size-1], and should
7321 // not be in order.
7322 unsigned Offset = 0;
7323 unsigned Max = 0;
7324 bool IsOrdered = true;
7325 assert(Indexes.empty() && "Expected empty order vector");
7326 do {
7327 unsigned Index;
7328 if (ParseUInt32(Index))
7329 return true;
7330
7331 // Update consistency checks.
7332 Offset += Index - Indexes.size();
7333 Max = std::max(Max, Index);
7334 IsOrdered &= Index == Indexes.size();
7335
7336 Indexes.push_back(Index);
7337 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
7338
7339 if (ParseToken(lltok::rbrace, "expected '}' here"))
7340 return true;
7341
7342 if (Indexes.size() < 2)
7343 return Error(Loc, "expected >= 2 uselistorder indexes");
7344 if (Offset != 0 || Max >= Indexes.size())
7345 return Error(Loc, "expected distinct uselistorder indexes in range [0, size)");
7346 if (IsOrdered)
7347 return Error(Loc, "expected uselistorder indexes to change the order");
7348
7349 return false;
7350}
7351
7352/// ParseUseListOrder
7353/// ::= 'uselistorder' Type Value ',' UseListOrderIndexes
7354bool LLParser::ParseUseListOrder(PerFunctionState *PFS) {
7355 SMLoc Loc = Lex.getLoc();
7356 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_uselistorder, "expected uselistorder directive"))
7357 return true;
7358
7359 Value *V;
7360 SmallVector<unsigned, 16> Indexes;
7361 if (ParseTypeAndValue(V, PFS) ||
7362 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in uselistorder directive") ||
7363 ParseUseListOrderIndexes(Indexes))
7364 return true;
7365
7366 return sortUseListOrder(V, Indexes, Loc);
7367}
7368
7369/// ParseUseListOrderBB
7370/// ::= 'uselistorder_bb' @foo ',' %bar ',' UseListOrderIndexes
7371bool LLParser::ParseUseListOrderBB() {
7372 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_uselistorder_bb);
7373 SMLoc Loc = Lex.getLoc();
7374 Lex.Lex();
7375
7376 ValID Fn, Label;
7377 SmallVector<unsigned, 16> Indexes;
7378 if (ParseValID(Fn) ||
7379 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in uselistorder_bb directive") ||
7380 ParseValID(Label) ||
7381 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected comma in uselistorder_bb directive") ||
7382 ParseUseListOrderIndexes(Indexes))
7383 return true;
7384
7385 // Check the function.
7386 GlobalValue *GV;
7387 if (Fn.Kind == ValID::t_GlobalName)
7388 GV = M->getNamedValue(Fn.StrVal);
7389 else if (Fn.Kind == ValID::t_GlobalID)
7390 GV = Fn.UIntVal < NumberedVals.size() ? NumberedVals[Fn.UIntVal] : nullptr;
7391 else
7392 return Error(Fn.Loc, "expected function name in uselistorder_bb");
7393 if (!GV)
7394 return Error(Fn.Loc, "invalid function forward reference in uselistorder_bb");
7395 auto *F = dyn_cast<Function>(GV);
7396 if (!F)
7397 return Error(Fn.Loc, "expected function name in uselistorder_bb");
7398 if (F->isDeclaration())
7399 return Error(Fn.Loc, "invalid declaration in uselistorder_bb");
7400
7401 // Check the basic block.
7402 if (Label.Kind == ValID::t_LocalID)
7403 return Error(Label.Loc, "invalid numeric label in uselistorder_bb");
7404 if (Label.Kind != ValID::t_LocalName)
7405 return Error(Label.Loc, "expected basic block name in uselistorder_bb");
7406 Value *V = F->getValueSymbolTable()->lookup(Label.StrVal);
7407 if (!V)
7408 return Error(Label.Loc, "invalid basic block in uselistorder_bb");
7409 if (!isa<BasicBlock>(V))
7410 return Error(Label.Loc, "expected basic block in uselistorder_bb");
7411
7412 return sortUseListOrder(V, Indexes, Loc);
7413}
7414
7415/// ModuleEntry
7416/// ::= 'module' ':' '(' 'path' ':' STRINGCONSTANT ',' 'hash' ':' Hash ')'
7417/// Hash ::= '(' UInt32 ',' UInt32 ',' UInt32 ',' UInt32 ',' UInt32 ')'
7418bool LLParser::ParseModuleEntry(unsigned ID) {
7419 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_module);
7420 Lex.Lex();
7421
7422 std::string Path;
7423 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7424 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
7425 ParseToken(lltok::kw_path, "expected 'path' here") ||
7426 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7427 ParseStringConstant(Path) ||
7428 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7429 ParseToken(lltok::kw_hash, "expected 'hash' here") ||
7430 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7431 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
7432 return true;
7433
7434 ModuleHash Hash;
7435 if (ParseUInt32(Hash[0]) || ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7436 ParseUInt32(Hash[1]) || ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7437 ParseUInt32(Hash[2]) || ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7438 ParseUInt32(Hash[3]) || ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7439 ParseUInt32(Hash[4]))
7440 return true;
7441
7442 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here") ||
7443 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7444 return true;
7445
7446 auto ModuleEntry = Index->addModule(Path, ID, Hash);
7447 ModuleIdMap[ID] = ModuleEntry->first();
7448
7449 return false;
7450}
7451
7452/// TypeIdEntry
7453/// ::= 'typeid' ':' '(' 'name' ':' STRINGCONSTANT ',' TypeIdSummary ')'
7454bool LLParser::ParseTypeIdEntry(unsigned ID) {
7455 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_typeid);
7456 Lex.Lex();
7457
7458 std::string Name;
7459 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7460 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
7461 ParseToken(lltok::kw_name, "expected 'name' here") ||
7462 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7463 ParseStringConstant(Name))
7464 return true;
7465
7466 TypeIdSummary &TIS = Index->getOrInsertTypeIdSummary(Name);
7467 if (ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7468 ParseTypeIdSummary(TIS) || ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7469 return true;
7470
7471 // Check if this ID was forward referenced, and if so, update the
7472 // corresponding GUIDs.
7473 auto FwdRefTIDs = ForwardRefTypeIds.find(ID);
7474 if (FwdRefTIDs != ForwardRefTypeIds.end()) {
7475 for (auto TIDRef : FwdRefTIDs->second) {
7476 assert(!*TIDRef.first &&
7477 "Forward referenced type id GUID expected to be 0");
7478 *TIDRef.first = GlobalValue::getGUID(Name);
7479 }
7480 ForwardRefTypeIds.erase(FwdRefTIDs);
7481 }
7482
7483 return false;
7484}

7486/// TypeIdSummary
7487/// ::= 'summary' ':' '(' TypeTestResolution [',' OptionalWpdResolutions]? ')'
7488bool LLParser::ParseTypeIdSummary(TypeIdSummary &TIS) {
7489 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_summary, "expected 'summary' here") ||
7490 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7491 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
7492 ParseTypeTestResolution(TIS.TTRes))
7493 return true;
7494
7495 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7496 // Expect optional wpdResolutions field
7497 if (ParseOptionalWpdResolutions(TIS.WPDRes))
7498 return true;
7499 }
7500
7501 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7502 return true;
7503
7504 return false;
7505}

7507/// TypeTestResolution
7508/// ::= 'typeTestRes' ':' '(' 'kind' ':'
7509/// ( 'unsat' | 'byteArray' | 'inline' | 'single' | 'allOnes' ) ','
7510/// 'sizeM1BitWidth' ':' SizeM1BitWidth [',' 'alignLog2' ':' UInt64]?
7511/// [',' 'sizeM1' ':' UInt64]? [',' 'bitMask' ':' UInt8]?
7512/// [',' 'inlinesBits' ':' UInt64]? ')'
7513bool LLParser::ParseTypeTestResolution(TypeTestResolution &TTRes) {
7514 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_typeTestRes, "expected 'typeTestRes' here") ||
7515 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7516 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
7517 ParseToken(lltok::kw_kind, "expected 'kind' here") ||
7518 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here"))
7519 return true;
7520
7521 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7522 case lltok::kw_unsat:
7523 TTRes.TheKind = TypeTestResolution::Unsat;
7524 break;
7525 case lltok::kw_byteArray:
7526 TTRes.TheKind = TypeTestResolution::ByteArray;
7527 break;
7528 case lltok::kw_inline:
7529 TTRes.TheKind = TypeTestResolution::Inline;
7530 break;
7531 case lltok::kw_single:
7532 TTRes.TheKind = TypeTestResolution::Single;
7533 break;
7534 case lltok::kw_allOnes:
7535 TTRes.TheKind = TypeTestResolution::AllOnes;
7536 break;
7537 default:
7538 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "unexpected TypeTestResolution kind");
7539 }
7540 Lex.Lex();
7541
7542 if (ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7543 ParseToken(lltok::kw_sizeM1BitWidth, "expected 'sizeM1BitWidth' here") ||
7544 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7545 ParseUInt32(TTRes.SizeM1BitWidth))
7546 return true;
7547
7548 // Parse optional fields
7549 while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7550 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7551 case lltok::kw_alignLog2:
7552 Lex.Lex();
7553 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") ||
7554 ParseUInt64(TTRes.AlignLog2))
7555 return true;
7556 break;
7557 case lltok::kw_sizeM1:
7558 Lex.Lex();
7559 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseUInt64(TTRes.SizeM1))
7560 return true;
7561 break;
7562 case lltok::kw_bitMask: {
7563 unsigned Val;
7564 Lex.Lex();
7565 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseUInt32(Val))
7566 return true;
7567 assert(Val <= 0xff);
7568 TTRes.BitMask = (uint8_t)Val;
7569 break;
7570 }
7571 case lltok::kw_inlineBits:
7572 Lex.Lex();
7573 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") ||
7574 ParseUInt64(TTRes.InlineBits))
7575 return true;
7576 break;
7577 default:
7578 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected optional TypeTestResolution field");
7579 }
7580 }
7581
7582 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7583 return true;
7584
7585 return false;
7586}

7588/// OptionalWpdResolutions
7589/// ::= 'wpsResolutions' ':' '(' WpdResolution [',' WpdResolution]* ')'
7590/// WpdResolution ::= '(' 'offset' ':' UInt64 ',' WpdRes ')'
7591bool LLParser::ParseOptionalWpdResolutions(
7592 std::map<uint64_t, WholeProgramDevirtResolution> &WPDResMap) {
7593 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_wpdResolutions, "expected 'wpdResolutions' here") ||
7594 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7595 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
7596 return true;
7597
7598 do {
7599 uint64_t Offset;
7600 WholeProgramDevirtResolution WPDRes;
7601 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
7602 ParseToken(lltok::kw_offset, "expected 'offset' here") ||
7603 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") || ParseUInt64(Offset) ||
7604 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") || ParseWpdRes(WPDRes) ||
7605 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7606 return true;
7607 WPDResMap[Offset] = WPDRes;
7608 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
7609
7610 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7611 return true;
7612
7613 return false;

7616/// WpdRes
7617/// ::= 'wpdRes' ':' '(' 'kind' ':' 'indir'
7618/// [',' OptionalResByArg]? ')'
7619/// ::= 'wpdRes' ':' '(' 'kind' ':' 'singleImpl'
7620/// ',' 'singleImplName' ':' STRINGCONSTANT ','
7621/// [',' OptionalResByArg]? ')'
7622/// ::= 'wpdRes' ':' '(' 'kind' ':' 'branchFunnel'
7623/// [',' OptionalResByArg]? ')'
7624bool LLParser::ParseWpdRes(WholeProgramDevirtResolution &WPDRes) {
7625 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_wpdRes, "expected 'wpdRes' here") ||
7626 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7627 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
7628 ParseToken(lltok::kw_kind, "expected 'kind' here") ||
7629 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here"))
7630 return true;
7631
7632 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7633 case lltok::kw_indir:
7634 WPDRes.TheKind = WholeProgramDevirtResolution::Indir;
7635 break;
7636 case lltok::kw_singleImpl:
7637 WPDRes.TheKind = WholeProgramDevirtResolution::SingleImpl;
7638 break;
7639 case lltok::kw_branchFunnel:
7640 WPDRes.TheKind = WholeProgramDevirtResolution::BranchFunnel;
7641 break;
7642 default:
7643 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "unexpected WholeProgramDevirtResolution kind");
7644 }
7645 Lex.Lex();
7646
7647 // Parse optional fields
7648 while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7649 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7650 case lltok::kw_singleImplName:
7651 Lex.Lex();
7652 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7653 ParseStringConstant(WPDRes.SingleImplName))
7654 return true;
7655 break;
7656 case lltok::kw_resByArg:
7657 if (ParseOptionalResByArg(WPDRes.ResByArg))
7658 return true;
7659 break;
7660 default:
7661 return Error(Lex.getLoc(),
7662 "expected optional WholeProgramDevirtResolution field");
7663 }
7664 }
7665
7666 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7667 return true;
7668
7669 return false;
7670}

7672/// OptionalResByArg
7673/// ::= 'wpdRes' ':' '(' ResByArg[, ResByArg]* ')'
7674/// ResByArg ::= Args ',' 'byArg' ':' '(' 'kind' ':'
7675/// ( 'indir' | 'uniformRetVal' | 'UniqueRetVal' |
7676/// 'virtualConstProp' )
7677/// [',' 'info' ':' UInt64]? [',' 'byte' ':' UInt32]?
7678/// [',' 'bit' ':' UInt32]? ')'
7679bool LLParser::ParseOptionalResByArg(
7680 std::map<std::vector<uint64_t>, WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg>
7681 &ResByArg) {
7682 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_resByArg, "expected 'resByArg' here") ||
7683 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7684 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
7685 return true;
7686
7687 do {
7688 std::vector<uint64_t> Args;
7689 if (ParseArgs(Args) || ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7690 ParseToken(lltok::kw_byArg, "expected 'byArg here") ||
7691 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7692 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
7693 ParseToken(lltok::kw_kind, "expected 'kind' here") ||
7694 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here"))
7695 return true;
7696
7697 WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg ByArg;
7698 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7699 case lltok::kw_indir:
7700 ByArg.TheKind = WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg::Indir;
7701 break;
7702 case lltok::kw_uniformRetVal:
7703 ByArg.TheKind = WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg::UniformRetVal;
7704 break;
7705 case lltok::kw_uniqueRetVal:
7706 ByArg.TheKind = WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg::UniqueRetVal;
7707 break;
7708 case lltok::kw_virtualConstProp:
7709 ByArg.TheKind = WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg::VirtualConstProp;
7710 break;
7711 default:
7712 return Error(Lex.getLoc(),
7713 "unexpected WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg kind");
7714 }
7715 Lex.Lex();
7716
7717 // Parse optional fields
7718 while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7719 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7720 case lltok::kw_info:
7721 Lex.Lex();
7722 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7723 ParseUInt64(ByArg.Info))
7724 return true;
7725 break;
7726 case lltok::kw_byte:
7727 Lex.Lex();
7728 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7729 ParseUInt32(ByArg.Byte))
7730 return true;
7731 break;
7732 case lltok::kw_bit:
7733 Lex.Lex();
7734 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7735 ParseUInt32(ByArg.Bit))
7736 return true;
7737 break;
7738 default:
7739 return Error(Lex.getLoc(),
7740 "expected optional whole program devirt field");
7741 }
7742 }
7743
7744 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7745 return true;
7746
7747 ResByArg[Args] = ByArg;
7748 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
7749
7750 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7751 return true;
7752
7753 return false;
7754}
7755
7756/// OptionalResByArg
7757/// ::= 'args' ':' '(' UInt64[, UInt64]* ')'
7758bool LLParser::ParseArgs(std::vector<uint64_t> &Args) {
7759 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_args, "expected 'args' here") ||
7760 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7761 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
7762 return true;
7763
7764 do {
7765 uint64_t Val;
7766 if (ParseUInt64(Val))
7767 return true;
7768 Args.push_back(Val);
7769 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
7770
7771 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7772 return true;
7773
7774 return false;
7775}
7776
7777static const auto FwdVIRef = (GlobalValueSummaryMapTy::value_type *)-8;
7778
7779static void resolveFwdRef(ValueInfo *Fwd, ValueInfo &Resolved) {
7780 bool ReadOnly = Fwd->isReadOnly();
7781 *Fwd = Resolved;
7782 if (ReadOnly)
7783 Fwd->setReadOnly();
7784}
7785
7786/// Stores the given Name/GUID and associated summary into the Index.
7787/// Also updates any forward references to the associated entry ID.
7788void LLParser::AddGlobalValueToIndex(
7789 std::string Name, GlobalValue::GUID GUID, GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage,
7790 unsigned ID, std::unique_ptr<GlobalValueSummary> Summary) {
7791 // First create the ValueInfo utilizing the Name or GUID.
7792 ValueInfo VI;
7793 if (GUID != 0) {
7794 assert(Name.empty());
7795 VI = Index->getOrInsertValueInfo(GUID);
7796 } else {
7797 assert(!Name.empty());
7798 if (M) {
7799 auto *GV = M->getNamedValue(Name);
7800 assert(GV);
7801 VI = Index->getOrInsertValueInfo(GV);
7802 } else {
7803 assert(
7804 (!GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage) || !SourceFileName.empty()) &&
7805 "Need a source_filename to compute GUID for local");
7806 GUID = GlobalValue::getGUID(
7807 GlobalValue::getGlobalIdentifier(Name, Linkage, SourceFileName));
7808 VI = Index->getOrInsertValueInfo(GUID, Index->saveString(Name));
7809 }
7810 }
7811
7812 // Resolve forward references from calls/refs
7813 auto FwdRefVIs = ForwardRefValueInfos.find(ID);
7814 if (FwdRefVIs != ForwardRefValueInfos.end()) {
7815 for (auto VIRef : FwdRefVIs->second) {
7816 assert(VIRef.first->getRef() == FwdVIRef &&
7817 "Forward referenced ValueInfo expected to be empty");
7818 resolveFwdRef(VIRef.first, VI);
7819 }
7820 ForwardRefValueInfos.erase(FwdRefVIs);
7821 }
7822
7823 // Resolve forward references from aliases
7824 auto FwdRefAliasees = ForwardRefAliasees.find(ID);
7825 if (FwdRefAliasees != ForwardRefAliasees.end()) {
7826 for (auto AliaseeRef : FwdRefAliasees->second) {
7827 assert(!AliaseeRef.first->hasAliasee() &&
7828 "Forward referencing alias already has aliasee");
7829 assert(Summary && "Aliasee must be a definition");
7830 AliaseeRef.first->setAliasee(VI, Summary.get());
7831 }
7832 ForwardRefAliasees.erase(FwdRefAliasees);
7833 }
7834
7835 // Add the summary if one was provided.
7836 if (Summary)
7837 Index->addGlobalValueSummary(VI, std::move(Summary));
7838
7839 // Save the associated ValueInfo for use in later references by ID.
7840 if (ID == NumberedValueInfos.size())
7841 NumberedValueInfos.push_back(VI);
7842 else {
7843 // Handle non-continuous numbers (to make test simplification easier).
7844 if (ID > NumberedValueInfos.size())
7845 NumberedValueInfos.resize(ID + 1);
7846 NumberedValueInfos[ID] = VI;
7847 }
7848}
7849
7850/// ParseGVEntry
7851/// ::= 'gv' ':' '(' ('name' ':' STRINGCONSTANT | 'guid' ':' UInt64)
7852/// [',' 'summaries' ':' Summary[',' Summary]* ]? ')'
7853/// Summary ::= '(' (FunctionSummary | VariableSummary | AliasSummary) ')'
7854bool LLParser::ParseGVEntry(unsigned ID) {
7855 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_gv);
7856 Lex.Lex();
7857
7858 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7859 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
7860 return true;
7861
7862 std::string Name;
7863 GlobalValue::GUID GUID = 0;
7864 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7865 case lltok::kw_name:
7866 Lex.Lex();
7867 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7868 ParseStringConstant(Name))
7869 return true;
7870 // Can't create GUID/ValueInfo until we have the linkage.
7871 break;
7872 case lltok::kw_guid:
7873 Lex.Lex();
7874 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") || ParseUInt64(GUID))
7875 return true;
7876 break;
7877 default:
7878 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected name or guid tag");
7879 }
7880
7881 if (!EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7882 // No summaries. Wrap up.
7883 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7884 return true;
7885 // This was created for a call to an external or indirect target.
7886 // A GUID with no summary came from a VALUE_GUID record, dummy GUID
7887 // created for indirect calls with VP. A Name with no GUID came from
7888 // an external definition. We pass ExternalLinkage since that is only
7889 // used when the GUID must be computed from Name, and in that case
7890 // the symbol must have external linkage.
7891 AddGlobalValueToIndex(Name, GUID, GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, ID,
7892 nullptr);
7893 return false;
7894 }
7895
7896 // Have a list of summaries
7897 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_summaries, "expected 'summaries' here") ||
7898 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here"))
7899 return true;
7900
7901 do {
7902 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
7903 return true;
7904 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7905 case lltok::kw_function:
7906 if (ParseFunctionSummary(Name, GUID, ID))
7907 return true;
7908 break;
7909 case lltok::kw_variable:
7910 if (ParseVariableSummary(Name, GUID, ID))
7911 return true;
7912 break;
7913 case lltok::kw_alias:
7914 if (ParseAliasSummary(Name, GUID, ID))
7915 return true;
7916 break;
7917 default:
7918 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected summary type");
7919 }
7920 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7921 return true;
7922 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
7923
7924 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7925 return true;
7926
7927 return false;
7928}
7929
7930/// FunctionSummary
7931/// ::= 'function' ':' '(' 'module' ':' ModuleReference ',' GVFlags
7932/// ',' 'insts' ':' UInt32 [',' OptionalFFlags]? [',' OptionalCalls]?
7933/// [',' OptionalTypeIdInfo]? [',' OptionalRefs]? ')'
7934bool LLParser::ParseFunctionSummary(std::string Name, GlobalValue::GUID GUID,
7935 unsigned ID) {
7936 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_function);
7937 Lex.Lex();
7938
7939 StringRef ModulePath;
7940 GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags GVFlags = GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags(
7941 /*Linkage=*/GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, /*NotEligibleToImport=*/false,
7942 /*Live=*/false, /*IsLocal=*/false, /*CanAutoHide=*/false);
7943 unsigned InstCount;
7944 std::vector<FunctionSummary::EdgeTy> Calls;
7945 FunctionSummary::TypeIdInfo TypeIdInfo;
7946 std::vector<ValueInfo> Refs;
7947 // Default is all-zeros (conservative values).
7948 FunctionSummary::FFlags FFlags = {};
7949 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
7950 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
7951 ParseModuleReference(ModulePath) ||
7952 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") || ParseGVFlags(GVFlags) ||
7953 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
7954 ParseToken(lltok::kw_insts, "expected 'insts' here") ||
7955 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") || ParseUInt32(InstCount))
7956 return true;
7957
7958 // Parse optional fields
7959 while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
7960 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
7961 case lltok::kw_funcFlags:
7962 if (ParseOptionalFFlags(FFlags))
7963 return true;
7964 break;
7965 case lltok::kw_calls:
7966 if (ParseOptionalCalls(Calls))
7967 return true;
7968 break;
7969 case lltok::kw_typeIdInfo:
7970 if (ParseOptionalTypeIdInfo(TypeIdInfo))
7971 return true;
7972 break;
7973 case lltok::kw_refs:
7974 if (ParseOptionalRefs(Refs))
7975 return true;
7976 break;
7977 default:
7978 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected optional function summary field");
7979 }
7980 }
7981
7982 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
7983 return true;
7984
7985 auto FS = llvm::make_unique<FunctionSummary>(
7986 GVFlags, InstCount, FFlags, /*EntryCount=*/0, std::move(Refs),
7987 std::move(Calls), std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeTests),
7988 std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeTestAssumeVCalls),
7989 std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeCheckedLoadVCalls),
7990 std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeTestAssumeConstVCalls),
7991 std::move(TypeIdInfo.TypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls));
7992
7993 FS->setModulePath(ModulePath);
7994
7995 AddGlobalValueToIndex(Name, GUID, (GlobalValue::LinkageTypes)GVFlags.Linkage,
7996 ID, std::move(FS));
7997
7998 return false;
7999}
8000
8001/// VariableSummary
8002/// ::= 'variable' ':' '(' 'module' ':' ModuleReference ',' GVFlags
8003/// [',' OptionalRefs]? ')'
8004bool LLParser::ParseVariableSummary(std::string Name, GlobalValue::GUID GUID,
8005 unsigned ID) {
8006 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_variable);
8007 Lex.Lex();
8008
8009 StringRef ModulePath;
8010 GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags GVFlags = GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags(
8011 /*Linkage=*/GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, /*NotEligibleToImport=*/false,
8012 /*Live=*/false, /*IsLocal=*/false, /*CanAutoHide=*/false);
8013 GlobalVarSummary::GVarFlags GVarFlags(/*ReadOnly*/ false);
8014 std::vector<ValueInfo> Refs;
8015 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8016 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8017 ParseModuleReference(ModulePath) ||
8018 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") || ParseGVFlags(GVFlags) ||
8019 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8020 ParseGVarFlags(GVarFlags))
8021 return true;
8022
8023 // Parse optional refs field
8024 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
8025 if (ParseOptionalRefs(Refs))
8026 return true;
8027 }
8028
8029 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8030 return true;
8031
8032 auto GS =
8033 llvm::make_unique<GlobalVarSummary>(GVFlags, GVarFlags, std::move(Refs));
8034
8035 GS->setModulePath(ModulePath);
8036
8037 AddGlobalValueToIndex(Name, GUID, (GlobalValue::LinkageTypes)GVFlags.Linkage,
8038 ID, std::move(GS));
8039
8040 return false;
8041}
8042
8043/// AliasSummary
8044/// ::= 'alias' ':' '(' 'module' ':' ModuleReference ',' GVFlags ','
8045/// 'aliasee' ':' GVReference ')'
8046bool LLParser::ParseAliasSummary(std::string Name, GlobalValue::GUID GUID,
8047 unsigned ID) {
8048 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_alias);
8049 LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8050 Lex.Lex();
8051
8052 StringRef ModulePath;
8053 GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags GVFlags = GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags(
8054 /*Linkage=*/GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, /*NotEligibleToImport=*/false,
8055 /*Live=*/false, /*IsLocal=*/false, /*CanAutoHide=*/false);
8056 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8057 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8058 ParseModuleReference(ModulePath) ||
8059 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") || ParseGVFlags(GVFlags) ||
8060 ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8061 ParseToken(lltok::kw_aliasee, "expected 'aliasee' here") ||
8062 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here"))
8063 return true;
8064
8065 ValueInfo AliaseeVI;
8066 unsigned GVId;
8067 if (ParseGVReference(AliaseeVI, GVId))
8068 return true;
8069
8070 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8071 return true;
8072
8073 auto AS = llvm::make_unique<AliasSummary>(GVFlags);
8074
8075 AS->setModulePath(ModulePath);
8076
8077 // Record forward reference if the aliasee is not parsed yet.
8078 if (AliaseeVI.getRef() == FwdVIRef) {
8079 auto FwdRef = ForwardRefAliasees.insert(
8080 std::make_pair(GVId, std::vector<std::pair<AliasSummary *, LocTy>>()));
8081 FwdRef.first->second.push_back(std::make_pair(AS.get(), Loc));
8082 } else {
8083 auto Summary = Index->findSummaryInModule(AliaseeVI, ModulePath);
8084 assert(Summary && "Aliasee must be a definition");
8085 AS->setAliasee(AliaseeVI, Summary);
8086 }
8087
8088 AddGlobalValueToIndex(Name, GUID, (GlobalValue::LinkageTypes)GVFlags.Linkage,
8089 ID, std::move(AS));
8090
8091 return false;
8092}
8093
8094/// Flag
8095/// ::= [0|1]
8096bool LLParser::ParseFlag(unsigned &Val) {
8097 if (Lex.getKind() != lltok::APSInt || Lex.getAPSIntVal().isSigned())
8098 return TokError("expected integer");
8099 Val = (unsigned)Lex.getAPSIntVal().getBoolValue();
8100 Lex.Lex();
8101 return false;
8102}
8103
8104/// OptionalFFlags
8105/// := 'funcFlags' ':' '(' ['readNone' ':' Flag]?
8106/// [',' 'readOnly' ':' Flag]? [',' 'noRecurse' ':' Flag]?
8107/// [',' 'returnDoesNotAlias' ':' Flag]? ')'
8108/// [',' 'noInline' ':' Flag]? ')'
8109bool LLParser::ParseOptionalFFlags(FunctionSummary::FFlags &FFlags) {
8110 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_funcFlags);
8111 Lex.Lex();
8112
8113 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' in funcFlags") |
8114 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in funcFlags"))
8115 return true;
8116
8117 do {
8118 unsigned Val = 0;
8119 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8120 case lltok::kw_readNone:
8121 Lex.Lex();
8122 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Val))
8123 return true;
8124 FFlags.ReadNone = Val;
8125 break;
8126 case lltok::kw_readOnly:
8127 Lex.Lex();
8128 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Val))
8129 return true;
8130 FFlags.ReadOnly = Val;
8131 break;
8132 case lltok::kw_noRecurse:
8133 Lex.Lex();
8134 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Val))
8135 return true;
8136 FFlags.NoRecurse = Val;
8137 break;
8138 case lltok::kw_returnDoesNotAlias:
8139 Lex.Lex();
8140 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Val))
8141 return true;
8142 FFlags.ReturnDoesNotAlias = Val;
8143 break;
8144 case lltok::kw_noInline:
8145 Lex.Lex();
8146 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Val))
8147 return true;
8148 FFlags.NoInline = Val;
8149 break;
8150 default:
8151 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected function flag type");
8152 }
8153 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8154
8155 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in funcFlags"))
8156 return true;
8157
8158 return false;
8159}
8160
8161/// OptionalCalls
8162/// := 'calls' ':' '(' Call [',' Call]* ')'
8163/// Call ::= '(' 'callee' ':' GVReference
8164/// [( ',' 'hotness' ':' Hotness | ',' 'relbf' ':' UInt32 )]? ')'
8165bool LLParser::ParseOptionalCalls(std::vector<FunctionSummary::EdgeTy> &Calls) {
8166 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_calls);
8167 Lex.Lex();
8168
8169 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' in calls") |
8170 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in calls"))
8171 return true;
8172
8173 IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
8174 // Parse each call edge
8175 do {
8176 ValueInfo VI;
8177 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in call") ||
8178 ParseToken(lltok::kw_callee, "expected 'callee' in call") ||
8179 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'"))
8180 return true;
8181
8182 LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8183 unsigned GVId;
8184 if (ParseGVReference(VI, GVId))
8185 return true;
8186
8187 CalleeInfo::HotnessType Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Unknown;
8188 unsigned RelBF = 0;
8189 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma)) {
8190 // Expect either hotness or relbf
8191 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_hotness)) {
8192 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseHotness(Hotness))
8193 return true;
8194 } else {
8195 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_relbf, "expected relbf") ||
8196 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseUInt32(RelBF))
8197 return true;
8198 }
8199 }
8200 // Keep track of the Call array index needing a forward reference.
8201 // We will save the location of the ValueInfo needing an update, but
8202 // can only do so once the std::vector is finalized.
8203 if (VI.getRef() == FwdVIRef)
8204 IdToIndexMap[GVId].push_back(std::make_pair(Calls.size(), Loc));
8205 Calls.push_back(FunctionSummary::EdgeTy{VI, CalleeInfo(Hotness, RelBF)});
8206
8207 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in call"))
8208 return true;
8209 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8210
8211 // Now that the Calls vector is finalized, it is safe to save the locations
8212 // of any forward GV references that need updating later.
8213 for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
8214 for (auto P : I.second) {
8215 assert(Calls[P.first].first.getRef() == FwdVIRef &&
8216 "Forward referenced ValueInfo expected to be empty");
8217 auto FwdRef = ForwardRefValueInfos.insert(std::make_pair(
8218 I.first, std::vector<std::pair<ValueInfo *, LocTy>>()));
8219 FwdRef.first->second.push_back(
8220 std::make_pair(&Calls[P.first].first, P.second));
8221 }
8222 }
8223
8224 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in calls"))
8225 return true;
8226
8227 return false;
8228}
8229
8230/// Hotness
8231/// := ('unknown'|'cold'|'none'|'hot'|'critical')
8232bool LLParser::ParseHotness(CalleeInfo::HotnessType &Hotness) {
8233 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8234 case lltok::kw_unknown:
8235 Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Unknown;
8236 break;
8237 case lltok::kw_cold:
8238 Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Cold;
8239 break;
8240 case lltok::kw_none:
8241 Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::None;
8242 break;
8243 case lltok::kw_hot:
8244 Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Hot;
8245 break;
8246 case lltok::kw_critical:
8247 Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Critical;
8248 break;
8249 default:
8250 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "invalid call edge hotness");
8251 }
8252 Lex.Lex();
8253 return false;
8254}
8255
8256/// OptionalRefs
8257/// := 'refs' ':' '(' GVReference [',' GVReference]* ')'
8258bool LLParser::ParseOptionalRefs(std::vector<ValueInfo> &Refs) {
8259 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_refs);
8260 Lex.Lex();
8261
8262 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' in refs") |
8263 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in refs"))
8264 return true;
8265
8266 struct ValueContext {
8267 ValueInfo VI;
8268 unsigned GVId;
8269 LocTy Loc;
8270 };
8271 std::vector<ValueContext> VContexts;
8272 // Parse each ref edge
8273 do {
8274 ValueContext VC;
8275 VC.Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8276 if (ParseGVReference(VC.VI, VC.GVId))
8277 return true;
8278 VContexts.push_back(VC);
8279 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8280
8281 // Sort value contexts so that ones with readonly ValueInfo are at the end
8282 // of VContexts vector. This is needed to match immutableRefCount() behavior.
8283 llvm::sort(VContexts, [](const ValueContext &VC1, const ValueContext &VC2) {
8284 return VC1.VI.isReadOnly() < VC2.VI.isReadOnly();
8285 });
8286
8287 IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
8288 for (auto &VC : VContexts) {
8289 // Keep track of the Refs array index needing a forward reference.
8290 // We will save the location of the ValueInfo needing an update, but
8291 // can only do so once the std::vector is finalized.
8292 if (VC.VI.getRef() == FwdVIRef)
8293 IdToIndexMap[VC.GVId].push_back(std::make_pair(Refs.size(), VC.Loc));
8294 Refs.push_back(VC.VI);
8295 }
8296
8297 // Now that the Refs vector is finalized, it is safe to save the locations
8298 // of any forward GV references that need updating later.
8299 for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
8300 for (auto P : I.second) {
8301 assert(Refs[P.first].getRef() == FwdVIRef &&
8302 "Forward referenced ValueInfo expected to be empty");
8303 auto FwdRef = ForwardRefValueInfos.insert(std::make_pair(
8304 I.first, std::vector<std::pair<ValueInfo *, LocTy>>()));
8305 FwdRef.first->second.push_back(std::make_pair(&Refs[P.first], P.second));
8306 }
8307 }
8308
8309 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in refs"))
8310 return true;
8311
8312 return false;
8313}
8314
8315/// OptionalTypeIdInfo
8316/// := 'typeidinfo' ':' '(' [',' TypeTests]? [',' TypeTestAssumeVCalls]?
8317/// [',' TypeCheckedLoadVCalls]? [',' TypeTestAssumeConstVCalls]?
8318/// [',' TypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls]? ')'
8319bool LLParser::ParseOptionalTypeIdInfo(
8320 FunctionSummary::TypeIdInfo &TypeIdInfo) {
8321 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_typeIdInfo);
8322 Lex.Lex();
8323
8324 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8325 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in typeIdInfo"))
8326 return true;
8327
8328 do {
8329 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8330 case lltok::kw_typeTests:
8331 if (ParseTypeTests(TypeIdInfo.TypeTests))
8332 return true;
8333 break;
8334 case lltok::kw_typeTestAssumeVCalls:
8335 if (ParseVFuncIdList(lltok::kw_typeTestAssumeVCalls,
8336 TypeIdInfo.TypeTestAssumeVCalls))
8337 return true;
8338 break;
8339 case lltok::kw_typeCheckedLoadVCalls:
8340 if (ParseVFuncIdList(lltok::kw_typeCheckedLoadVCalls,
8341 TypeIdInfo.TypeCheckedLoadVCalls))
8342 return true;
8343 break;
8344 case lltok::kw_typeTestAssumeConstVCalls:
8345 if (ParseConstVCallList(lltok::kw_typeTestAssumeConstVCalls,
8346 TypeIdInfo.TypeTestAssumeConstVCalls))
8347 return true;
8348 break;
8349 case lltok::kw_typeCheckedLoadConstVCalls:
8350 if (ParseConstVCallList(lltok::kw_typeCheckedLoadConstVCalls,
8351 TypeIdInfo.TypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls))
8352 return true;
8353 break;
8354 default:
8355 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "invalid typeIdInfo list type");
8356 }
8357 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8358
8359 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in typeIdInfo"))
8360 return true;
8361
8362 return false;
8363}

8365/// TypeTests
8366/// ::= 'typeTests' ':' '(' (SummaryID | UInt64)
8367/// [',' (SummaryID | UInt64)]* ')'
8368bool LLParser::ParseTypeTests(std::vector<GlobalValue::GUID> &TypeTests) {
8369 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_typeTests);
8370 Lex.Lex();
8371
8372 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8373 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' in typeIdInfo"))
8374 return true;
8375
8376 IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
8377 do {
8378 GlobalValue::GUID GUID = 0;
8379 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::SummaryID) {
8380 unsigned ID = Lex.getUIntVal();
8381 LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8382 // Keep track of the TypeTests array index needing a forward reference.
8383 // We will save the location of the GUID needing an update, but
8384 // can only do so once the std::vector is finalized.
8385 IdToIndexMap[ID].push_back(std::make_pair(TypeTests.size(), Loc));
8386 Lex.Lex();
8387 } else if (ParseUInt64(GUID))
8388 return true;
8389 TypeTests.push_back(GUID);
8390 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8391
8392 // Now that the TypeTests vector is finalized, it is safe to save the
8393 // locations of any forward GV references that need updating later.
8394 for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
8395 for (auto P : I.second) {
8396 assert(TypeTests[P.first] == 0 &&
8397 "Forward referenced type id GUID expected to be 0");
8398 auto FwdRef = ForwardRefTypeIds.insert(std::make_pair(
8399 I.first, std::vector<std::pair<GlobalValue::GUID *, LocTy>>()));
8400 FwdRef.first->second.push_back(
8401 std::make_pair(&TypeTests[P.first], P.second));
8402 }
8403 }
8404
8405 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' in typeIdInfo"))
8406 return true;
8407
8408 return false;
8409}

8411/// VFuncIdList
8412/// ::= Kind ':' '(' VFuncId [',' VFuncId]* ')'
8413bool LLParser::ParseVFuncIdList(
8414 lltok::Kind Kind, std::vector<FunctionSummary::VFuncId> &VFuncIdList) {
8415 assert(Lex.getKind() == Kind);
8416 Lex.Lex();
8417
8418 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8419 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
8420 return true;
8421
8422 IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
8423 do {
8424 FunctionSummary::VFuncId VFuncId;
8425 if (ParseVFuncId(VFuncId, IdToIndexMap, VFuncIdList.size()))
8426 return true;
8427 VFuncIdList.push_back(VFuncId);
8428 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8429
8430 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8431 return true;
8432
8433 // Now that the VFuncIdList vector is finalized, it is safe to save the
8434 // locations of any forward GV references that need updating later.
8435 for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
8436 for (auto P : I.second) {
8437 assert(VFuncIdList[P.first].GUID == 0 &&
8438 "Forward referenced type id GUID expected to be 0");
8439 auto FwdRef = ForwardRefTypeIds.insert(std::make_pair(
8440 I.first, std::vector<std::pair<GlobalValue::GUID *, LocTy>>()));
8441 FwdRef.first->second.push_back(
8442 std::make_pair(&VFuncIdList[P.first].GUID, P.second));
8443 }
8444 }
8445
8446 return false;
8447}

8449/// ConstVCallList
8450/// ::= Kind ':' '(' ConstVCall [',' ConstVCall]* ')'
8451bool LLParser::ParseConstVCallList(
8452 lltok::Kind Kind,
8453 std::vector<FunctionSummary::ConstVCall> &ConstVCallList) {
8454 assert(Lex.getKind() == Kind);
8455 Lex.Lex();
8456
8457 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8458 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
8459 return true;
8460
8461 IdToIndexMapType IdToIndexMap;
8462 do {
8463 FunctionSummary::ConstVCall ConstVCall;
8464 if (ParseConstVCall(ConstVCall, IdToIndexMap, ConstVCallList.size()))
8465 return true;
8466 ConstVCallList.push_back(ConstVCall);
8467 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8468
8469 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8470 return true;
8471
8472 // Now that the ConstVCallList vector is finalized, it is safe to save the
8473 // locations of any forward GV references that need updating later.
8474 for (auto I : IdToIndexMap) {
8475 for (auto P : I.second) {
8476 assert(ConstVCallList[P.first].VFunc.GUID == 0 &&
8477 "Forward referenced type id GUID expected to be 0");
8478 auto FwdRef = ForwardRefTypeIds.insert(std::make_pair(
8479 I.first, std::vector<std::pair<GlobalValue::GUID *, LocTy>>()));
8480 FwdRef.first->second.push_back(
8481 std::make_pair(&ConstVCallList[P.first].VFunc.GUID, P.second));
8482 }
8483 }
8484
8485 return false;
8486}

8488/// ConstVCall
8489/// ::= '(' VFuncId ',' Args ')'
8490bool LLParser::ParseConstVCall(FunctionSummary::ConstVCall &ConstVCall,
8491 IdToIndexMapType &IdToIndexMap, unsigned Index) {
8492 if (ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8493 ParseVFuncId(ConstVCall.VFunc, IdToIndexMap, Index))
8494 return true;
8495
8496 if (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma))
8497 if (ParseArgs(ConstVCall.Args))
8498 return true;
8499
8500 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8501 return true;
8502
8503 return false;
8504}

8506/// VFuncId
8507/// ::= 'vFuncId' ':' '(' (SummaryID | 'guid' ':' UInt64) ','
8508/// 'offset' ':' UInt64 ')'
8509bool LLParser::ParseVFuncId(FunctionSummary::VFuncId &VFuncId,
8510 IdToIndexMapType &IdToIndexMap, unsigned Index) {
8511 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_vFuncId);
8512 Lex.Lex();
8513
8514 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8515 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
8516 return true;
8517
8518 if (Lex.getKind() == lltok::SummaryID) {
8519 VFuncId.GUID = 0;
8520 unsigned ID = Lex.getUIntVal();
8521 LocTy Loc = Lex.getLoc();
8522 // Keep track of the array index needing a forward reference.
8523 // We will save the location of the GUID needing an update, but
8524 // can only do so once the caller's std::vector is finalized.
8525 IdToIndexMap[ID].push_back(std::make_pair(Index, Loc));
8526 Lex.Lex();
8527 } else if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_guid, "expected 'guid' here") ||
8528 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8529 ParseUInt64(VFuncId.GUID))
8530 return true;
8531
8532 if (ParseToken(lltok::comma, "expected ',' here") ||
8533 ParseToken(lltok::kw_offset, "expected 'offset' here") ||
8534 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8535 ParseUInt64(VFuncId.Offset) ||
8536 ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8537 return true;
8538
8539 return false;
8540}

8542/// GVFlags
8543/// ::= 'flags' ':' '(' 'linkage' ':' OptionalLinkageAux ','
8544/// 'notEligibleToImport' ':' Flag ',' 'live' ':' Flag ','
8545/// 'dsoLocal' ':' Flag ',' 'canAutoHide' ':' Flag ')'
8546bool LLParser::ParseGVFlags(GlobalValueSummary::GVFlags &GVFlags) {
8547 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_flags);
8548 Lex.Lex();
8549
8550 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8551 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here"))
8552 return true;
8553
8554 do {
8555 unsigned Flag = 0;
8556 switch (Lex.getKind()) {
8557 case lltok::kw_linkage:
8558 Lex.Lex();
8559 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'"))
8560 return true;
8561 bool HasLinkage;
8562 GVFlags.Linkage = parseOptionalLinkageAux(Lex.getKind(), HasLinkage);
8563 assert(HasLinkage && "Linkage not optional in summary entry");
8564 Lex.Lex();
8565 break;
8566 case lltok::kw_notEligibleToImport:
8567 Lex.Lex();
8568 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Flag))
8569 return true;
8570 GVFlags.NotEligibleToImport = Flag;
8571 break;
8572 case lltok::kw_live:
8573 Lex.Lex();
8574 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Flag))
8575 return true;
8576 GVFlags.Live = Flag;
8577 break;
8578 case lltok::kw_dsoLocal:
8579 Lex.Lex();
8580 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Flag))
8581 return true;
8582 GVFlags.DSOLocal = Flag;
8583 break;
8584 case lltok::kw_canAutoHide:
8585 Lex.Lex();
8586 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':'") || ParseFlag(Flag))
8587 return true;
8588 GVFlags.CanAutoHide = Flag;
8589 break;
8590 default:
8591 return Error(Lex.getLoc(), "expected gv flag type");
8592 }
8593 } while (EatIfPresent(lltok::comma));
8594
8595 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8596 return true;
8597
8598 return false;
8599}

8601/// GVarFlags
8602/// ::= 'varFlags' ':' '(' 'readonly' ':' Flag ')'
8603bool LLParser::ParseGVarFlags(GlobalVarSummary::GVarFlags &GVarFlags) {
8604 assert(Lex.getKind() == lltok::kw_varFlags);
8605 Lex.Lex();
8606
8607 unsigned Flag = 0;
8608 if (ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8609 ParseToken(lltok::lparen, "expected '(' here") ||
8610 ParseToken(lltok::kw_readonly, "expected 'readonly' here") ||
8611 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here"))
8612 return true;
8613
8614 ParseFlag(Flag);
8615 GVarFlags.ReadOnly = Flag;
8616
8617 if (ParseToken(lltok::rparen, "expected ')' here"))
8618 return true;
8619 return false;
8620}

8622/// ModuleReference
8623/// ::= 'module' ':' UInt
8624bool LLParser::ParseModuleReference(StringRef &ModulePath) {
8625 // Parse module id.
8626 if (ParseToken(lltok::kw_module, "expected 'module' here") ||
8627 ParseToken(lltok::colon, "expected ':' here") ||
8628 ParseToken(lltok::SummaryID, "expected module ID"))
8629 return true;
8630
8631 unsigned ModuleID = Lex.getUIntVal();
8632 auto I = ModuleIdMap.find(ModuleID);
8633 // We should have already parsed all module IDs
8634 assert(I != ModuleIdMap.end());
8635 ModulePath = I->second;
8636 return false;
8637}
8638
8639/// GVReference
8640/// ::= SummaryID
8641bool LLParser::ParseGVReference(ValueInfo &VI, unsigned &GVId) {
8642 bool ReadOnly = EatIfPresent(lltok::kw_readonly);
8643 if (ParseToken(lltok::SummaryID, "expected GV ID"))
8644 return true;
8645
8646 GVId = Lex.getUIntVal();
8647 // Check if we already have a VI for this GV
8648 if (GVId < NumberedValueInfos.size()) {
8649 assert(NumberedValueInfos[GVId].getRef() != FwdVIRef);
8650 VI = NumberedValueInfos[GVId];
8651 } else
8652 // We will create a forward reference to the stored location.
8653 VI = ValueInfo(false, FwdVIRef);
8654
8655 if (ReadOnly)
8656 VI.setReadOnly();
8657 return false;
8658}
